<title>May_1993: Stockpiling weapons</title>
<h1>Stockpiling weapons</h1>
Tony Dyson (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>24 May 1993 09:52:23 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#246">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#246">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#246">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#246">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0247.html">Dan Hamstra: "Stockpiling weapons"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0245.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: The White Lie (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Consider an Adventist college with five hundred indoor students. If every one<br>
of these students were to own a firearm, that would amount to five hundred<br>
weapons within quite a small space. Would this be considered stockpiling<br>
weapons? I myself would certainly feel as though I were in an armoury, or<br>
at least in a military training camp. So to me, the Branch Davidians had an<br>
attitude to weapons quite different to the church at large, even to the world<br>
at large.<br>
<p>
Mind you, what they predicted did occur, ie they were invaded with force by<br>
an armed adversary. Self-fulfilling prophecy??<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
