<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;At the risk of being considered uncultured by the purists, have you</i><br>
<i>&gt;considered a synthesizer instead of an organ for your church, Steve?</i><br>
<i>&gt;Lola</i><br>
<i>&gt;Aagaard@Morekypr</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;[I wouldn't mind at all but I think our current worship style doesn't </i><br>
<i>&gt;lend itself well to that.  And as for Elmhurst SDA, no one is suggesting</i><br>
<i>&gt;a tracker.  We have neither the money nor the right space.  SCT]</i><br>
<p>
I have sat back and read most of the spew about organs that have<br>
appeared here in the last few months.  Maybe it is living away from the<br>
'cultured' areas of the world, but for the life of me I can not<br>
understand why an expensive organ is needed.<br>
<p>
It would seem to me that the money could be used for so many more<br>
important worth while means.  One that comes to mind is the lack of<br>
shortwave radios stations, like the one on Guam, which is used to send<br>
the message to Asia.<br>
<p>
Other means for the money could be used also.  I am sure many of you<br>
could think of ways to spend it other than on a new organ.<br>
<p>
Like I said before, I guess I just dont understand...<br>
<p>
