<title>May_1993: ATF raid at Waco</title>
<h1>ATF raid at Waco</h1>
Alan Fargusson (<i>70751.2436@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>24 May 93 12:16:04 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#264">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#264">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#264">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#264">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0265.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: The White Lie (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0263.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0283.html">Woody Baker: "Re: ATF raid at Waco"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Last night 60 minutes re-ran their story on sexual harassment in the ATF.  I<br>
had seen the story before, but I watched it again anyway.  At the end the said<br>
that the agents involved in the sexual harassment case thought that the raid in<br>
Waco was staged to get positive publicity for the ATF.  I had heard some<br>
negative thoughts on the motivation for the raid, but this was the first one<br>
that sounded credible to me, since it comes from prior and current ATF agents. <br>
I had thought that the raid was justified, but now I am beginning to think<br>
maybe it wasn't.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
