On May 24, 12:41pm, Susan Harrington wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: Re: sdas and guns</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I think that we will give the interpretation to Bible texts that reinforce our</i><br>
previously formed opinions.  We will search to find texts that make us<br>
<i>&gt; look good in the positions we have chosen to assume in life.  We will attempt</i><br>
<i>&gt; to use the Holy One to strengthen our humanly defined position even if it</i><br>
<i>&gt; means that we are subjugating another human being.</i><br>
<p>
Who is subjugating whom??  The person breaking and entering the sanctity of my<br>
home with the intent to harm my family ...or me?<br>
<p>
As for which came first, my "previously formed opinions" on the use of guns by<br>
SDAs or my upbringing and Bible teachings regarding the sanctity of life, I<br>
would have to definetly say the later.  And contrary to what you may belive, my<br>
opinions on SDAs and guns is not as "formed' as you are leading people to think,<br>
hence the reason for my post requesting texts &amp; interpretations from others on<br>
_both_ sides of the issue.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
