<title>May_1993: RE: Gun, Guns</title>
<h1>RE: Gun, Guns</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 24 May 93 15:46:40 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#222">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#222">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#222">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#222">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0223.html">Steven Timm: "Order in  Chaos"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0221.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Doctor/nurse/preacher/teacher/dentist/lawyer"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On May 23, 10:11am, "lsusers" wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: Guns, Guns</i><br>
<i>&gt; Hello SDAnetters:</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; What is it with the American obsession with guns?  Did any of you see</i><br>
<i>&gt; the Nightline program last week, where Ted interviewed some folk on</i><br>
<i>&gt; this subject?  If I am not mistaken, the statistics indicate that in</i><br>
<i>&gt; the USA, tens of thousands of people die every year as a result of</i><br>
<i>&gt; hand gun violence, whereas in Canada, Japan and Britain, less than</i><br>
<i>&gt; 70, (yes 7-0-) die a year.  Yet most Americans can see nothing</i><br>
<i>&gt; unusual or catastrophic about those figures.</i><br>
<p>
<p>
Yes it is a tragedy, but the problem (IMHO) is due to lack of respect for and<br>
education of proper handling and storage of guns AND a law enforcement system<br>
that in ineffective at removing the right to bear arms to those who have<br>
_violated_ their right by using guns in an unlawful manner (theft, murder, etc).<br>
<p>
I would not call it an obsession, but a strong feeling regarding our right to<br>
own guns.  The US is one of the few countries in the world that still allows<br>
this right.  Many people lost their lives gaining and then protecting that<br>
right.  We don't take this right lightly, but value it.  Unfortunately, as with<br>
all freedoms, people eventually lose their respect of their God given freedoms<br>
and abuse them.  This does not mean the freedoms should be taken away from<br>
all...just those who abuse these freedoms.<br>
<p>
Many anti-gunners think the solution is to create more laws to remove these<br>
freedoms to own guns.  But the problem with that is, another law won't stop a<br>
law-breaker.  Therefore, a new law simply restricts and hence punishes those of<br>
us who choose to abide by the laws already in place.<br>
<p>
Incidently, if numbers of needless deaths is what concerns you, then please take<br>
a closer look at the number of people that die in the USA &amp; other countries as a<br>
result of alchohol (drunk driving, siroesis of the liver, etc).  It far<br>
outnumbers the quantity of those killed by guns.  Yet, do we hear of laws to<br>
outlaw alchohol?<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<p>
<p>
