<!-- body="start" -->
Outlawing alcohol is a bit down the road.  You &gt;do&lt; hear voices asking<br>
for the first steps (ie. responsible advertising... if it's potentially lethal<br>
STATE IT!).  The special interest groups of the alcohol and tobacco<br>
industry have been kicking and screaming all the way.<br>
[I remind our readers that alcohol was in fact outlawed for almost <br>
10 years during the 1920's.  SCT]<br>
<p>
Gun control is an attempt to band-aid and ulcer.  The real problems are<br>
things which drive people to live by the gun or kill by the gun.  A few of<br>
them are:<br>
1) Poverty is first and foremost, GREED is the flip side of that<br>
2) People who don't know how to resolve differences in a peaceful way<br>
3) People who'd rather hide behind gun ownership rights, than address<br>
numbers 1 and 2<br>
4) The lost hope on the part of "the poor"<br>
<p>
It probably isn't a coincidence that money and how we treat "the poor" is<br>
spoken of so frequently scripture.<br>
<p>
Marcus@microsoft<br>
