<title>May_1993: Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC (fwd)</title>
<h1>Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC (fwd)</h1>
Harvey Brenneise (<i>brneise@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 25 May 1993 14:22:15 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#262">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#262">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#262">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#262">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0263.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0261.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Guns, Guns"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0186.html">Randall A Helzerman: "Censored Newsgroups @ WWC (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I think a key factor in eliminating this newsgroup though, comes from</i><br>
<i>&gt; the following section of the FAQ:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Judgements of sexual behavior should not be made.  ASAR readers run the gamut</i><br>
<i>&gt; from heterosexual to homosexual and everything in between.  No matter what your</i><br>
<i>&gt; orientation is, you have as much right as anyone to participate in ASAR, and as</i><br>
<i>&gt; little right to criticize someone else's sexuality as you would give to them.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; ***********************</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I think the preceding statement does justify the canceling of this</i><br>
<i>&gt; newsgroup, in that WWC is trying to get rid of newsgroups which</i><br>
<i>&gt; contradict the beliefs of SDA's.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I'm glad that the library I work for does not cancel subscriptions for<br>
the reason given above.  As I've thought about this, I don't think<br>
subscribing to newsgroups on a network is that different from<br>
periodicals in the library.  The job of selection is a positive one in<br>
which one chooses that which contributes to the institutional mission.<br>
Pronography and items of prurient interest do not, so are not selected.<br>
This is different than censorship.  Our library subscribes to journals<br>
which contradict SDA beliefs.  We could hardly be a university and not<br>
do so.<br>
<p>
Harvey Brenneise<br>
Head Reference Librarian<br>
Andrews University<br>
(brneise@andrews.edu)<br>
