<title>May_1993: Re: FW: Bible and Homosexuality</title>
<h1>Re: FW: Bible and Homosexuality</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 25 May 93 17:17:35 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#253">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#253">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#253">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#253">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0254.html">Steve Hix: "Re: sdas and guns"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0252.html">Tony Dyson: "EGW and Scripture"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0228.html">Marcus Stringer: "FW: Bible and Homosexuality"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0269.html">David Klein - EECS: "Homosexuality..."</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve, you bring up valid concerns which many people have, including<br>
those closest to homosexual people and homosexuals themselves.<br>
A rule worth remembering:  Never be a reflector of other people's thoughts<br>
and biases.  If you have thoughts and biases, take responsibility for them,<br>
be ready to qualify them and answer for them.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;We have inborn tendencies to all sorts of sin, stealing, lying, cheating,</i><br>
<i>&gt;you name it.  God sent not his son into the world to condemn the world,</i><br>
<i>&gt;but that the world through Him might be saved.</i><br>
<p>
This statement seems to simplify homosexuality to the point of being<br>
a case of selfishness and self-seeking equal to "stealing, lying, and <br>
cheating."<br>
Are you ready to qualify your thoughts and biases?  What are the underlying<br>
issues in stealing, lying, and cheating?  Are the traits of <br>
selfishness, telling<br>
untruths to cover oneself found in the homosexual identity itself?<br>
<p>
Maybe getting back to basics isn't bad, a basics which goes beyond<br>
"Adam and Eve".  WHAT ARE RELATIONSHIPS?  ARE THEY A GIFT FROM<br>
GOD?  ARE THEY SUPPOSED TO DRAW US TO A BETTER<br>
UNDERSTANDING *OF* AND RELATIONSHIP *WITH* GOD?  CAN THE<br>
GOD-GIVEN POWER OF CHOICE AND UNDERSTANDING BE EXPRESSED<br>
IN THESE RELATIONSHIPS?  ARE THEY REFLECTIONS OF THE<br>
COVENANT LOVE-RELATIONSHIP GOD HAS WITH HUMANS?  We might<br>
begin to find answers by addressing these questions.<br>
<p>
Perhaps we pay lip-service to Genesis 1 when it fits our needs, never allowing<br>
'woman' to be as equally "in the image of God" as 'man'.  A lot of it <br>
is cultural.<br>
What Jesus did, and said about women while on earth would have crashed<br>
like LED if it were done during earlier times in history (read: the <br>
fullness of time,<br>
the time being right).  Furthermore, it might not be a coincidence that <br>
God's call<br>
to homosexuals is happening at such a time as this (fullness of time).<br>
<p>
God's character as Creator can and is expressed in other ways than<br>
procreation.  This is not to say that procreation is of _low esteem_, <br>
it should be<br>
esteemed higher, much higher than it is currently.  Many of these other ways,<br>
"lower animals" can not duplicate.  Besides, some of the procreators are<br>
giving birth to homosexual children... now what do we do for the procreators<br>
who want to CREATE a loving and supportive world for their children?<br>
<p>
As the military of many a country show us, homosexuals have been nearly<br>
everywhere _already_.  So I don't doubt that they have been, are now, and will<br>
be teaching in our schools.  Shouldn't it be something to praise God for,<br>
instead of fearing the "unknown" - they still love God and seek to serve Him?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Do "normal individuals" plaster the campus restrooms with graffiti saying</i><br>
<i>&gt;where and when anonymous sexual encounters may be had?</i><br>
<i>&gt;Some say that the oppression came and forced the gays underground to</i><br>
<i>&gt;the various risky behaviors that they take.  It seems to me that this may</i><br>
<i>&gt;be revisionist history.</i><br>
<p>
"Normal individuals" do lots of things which can be questioned, and should<br>
be.  I suspect that when we question such a thing as anonymous sexual<br>
encounters, we might find a lot more than we expect.  We also might hear a<br>
call to action other than "police the area" (band-aid on ulcer).  One thing<br>
you might do, is to sponsor or assist in alternative non-erotic social,<br>
"community", or religious groups for gay and lesbian people.  And there are<br>
plenty of things in "history" which could use revision, or "telling the <br>
_whole_<br>
story" (ie:  US foreign relations, USSR'nt, women, race and more).<br>
So revising history is not an 'evil', unless someone perceiving her/himself to<br>
be an "insider", thinks that her/his place in life, gained through the <br>
partial truth,<br>
will be threatened by the WHOLE.<br>
<p>
Here's to the real lives, of real people restored to a right <br>
relationship with a<br>
REAL GOD - as expressed in Christ Jesus.<br>
<p>
Marcus -&gt;  How ARE homosexual students treated on our Adventist college<br>
campuses by faculty/staff/students?<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
