<title>May_1993: Re:  FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?</title>
<h1>Re:  FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 26 May 93 02:11:22 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#263">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#263">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#263">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#263">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0264.html">Alan Fargusson: "ATF raid at Waco"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0262.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0238.html">Marcus Stringer: "FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0268.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  FW:  female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Marcus writes:<br>
<i>&gt;HOW, exactly are we to love the sinner but hate the sin?  How, are we</i><br>
<i>&gt;suppose to know when, I assume, "Godly love" for the 'sinner' should</i><br>
<i>&gt;end, and condoning begin?  Can you, or anyone help in explaining</i><br>
<i>&gt;this?</i><br>
<p>
I'm not sure what you mean, but i think we should show "Godly love" to<br>
everyone, all the time, it should never "end" and we should never condone<br>
sin at all. God loves us sinners, but that does not mean that He loves our<br>
sin. He loves us not because of who or what we are, but because of who He<br>
is. God _is_ love. I still don't see what the perceived contradiction is.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;There are people who are out to make sure that homosexuals do not have</i><br>
<i>&gt;jobs or homes... (especially if they are honest about who they are) where is</i><br>
<i>&gt;the Bible on this, where is the Church on this? If they support this type of</i><br>
<i>&gt;anti-gay work, why are they silent? If they reject it, why are they silent?</i><br>
<i>&gt;People are perishing, now isn't the time to be silent.</i><br>
<p>
Well, my own opinion is that if they are out of a job, we should help them<br>
find one, not because they are homosexual, but because they are people in<br>
need of work. Also, it is not the business of the church to go on a witch<br>
hunt or to stone sabbath breakers etc. The church seems to be silent i<br>
suppose, because it does not want to abe identified with either of the two<br>
sides which seem to be at war: the millitant anti gay movement or the gay<br>
activists. Both of these movements have the spirit of the enemy in them.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;The Sodom story isn't a good one to use against homosexuality.....</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;of the population...  Was Sodom an all-gay town?  If anything, the</i><br>
<i>&gt;destruction of Sodom is due to committing homosexual [rape] on</i><br>
<i>&gt;strangers if not angels.  Rape is more an issue of "power", self exalting,</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Couple this with the societal beliefs regarding gender status, and the</i><br>
<i>&gt;assumed meaning for the destruction applies less fittingly.</i><br>
<p>
Well, it was probably the sum total of all the evil in Sodom, that filled up<br>
its cup of wrath against it. The attempted rape of the angels was only the<br>
last straw. However, the fact that the sexual perversion of the Sodomites<br>
was one of the sins that added up to its destruction is evident, because<br>
elsewhere in the bible, sexual impurity is denounced in no uncertain terms.<br>
See also Jude 1:7.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
------------------------------------<br>
beng.tang@f622.n600.z6.fidonet.org<br>
