<title>May_1993: Pigs and the FLU</title>
<h1>Pigs and the FLU</h1>
<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i><br>
<i>Wed, 26 May 93 07:37:01 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#281">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#281">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#281">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#281">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0282.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Pigs and the FLU"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0280.html">Steven Timm: "Biases"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0287.html">Daryl Starr: "Re: Pigs and the FLU"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
While in the dentists office I read an article in Discover magazine.<br>
It is a laymens science journal.<br>
<p>
This is somewhat preliminary science that seems to have some real<br>
substance to it -- more research needed.  The discovery being that<br>
pigs are excellent "mixing vessels" for the flu virus.  Pigs can<br>
catch human flu virus that other animals cannot catch.  Pigs can<br>
catch bird flu that other animals cannot catch.  Perhaps the flu<br>
of other animals.  What happens is that these flu virus take hold<br>
in a single host, the pig, and then genetics takes over.  So, the<br>
farmer goes out to feed his hogs.  He coughs his "cold" into his<br>
friendly hogs face.  The hog incubates that flu with other flu<br>
virus from birds, etc, and a few weeks later the farmer heads out<br>
to feed his hogs and the hog coughs the new virus into the farmers<br>
face.  The new virus can turn out to be deadly and can soon be<br>
sweeping around the world.  There is pretty good evidence, from<br>
DNA analysis, that some of the more deadly flus of recent years<br>
are very likely human/bird --&gt; hog --&gt; human in origen.<br>
<p>
The Bible says ". . . . . and none of these diseases will come<br>
nigh unto you".<br>
<p>
During the dark ages the Jews were often crowded into European<br>
ghetos.  Epidemiology would say they should have experienced a<br>
higher mortality rate.  But when the plagues of Europe swept through<br>
town the Jews did not die like flies like the rest of Europe.<br>
Why, because of the health laws of Moses.  In many cases this<br>
was used against them.  Mobs were insited against the Jews on<br>
the theory that the Jews must be the instigators of the disease<br>
because they were the only ones not dying of the disease.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
