<title>May_1993: SDAs and homosexuality.</title>
<h1>SDAs and homosexuality.</h1>
Noe Torres | ECISD (<i>noe@tenet.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 26 May 1993 08:03:19 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#272">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#272">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#272">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#272">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0273.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Homosexuality..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0271.html">Alvin Vitangcol: "Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Dear SDA Netters,<br>
<p>
For weeks I have been reading messages on SDANet which generally defend<br>
homosexuals and condemn heterosexuals.  I have found the arguments used to<br>
defend homosexuals very subtle and very interesting.  Some have<br>
raised accusations against God and against His character for being<br>
"unfair" to homosexuals, but the most profound accusations have been made<br>
against God's Church for mistreating homosexuals.  Arguments have been<br>
made that "love" is all that matters and that as long as homosexuals<br>
"love" their partners and don't "rape" them, homosexuality should be<br>
acceptable to God.  An attitude of "live and let live" has been expressed<br>
toward gays.  Some have openly stated that their interpretation of the<br>
Bible allows for homosexuality and that Christians have as much right to a<br>
pro-homosexual interpretation of the Bible as to any other interpretation.<br>
<p>
Commendable views have been expressed, such as that Christians should not<br>
be hostile or condemnatory toward gays and that sexual perversion exists<br>
among heterosexuals.  <br>
<p>
Still, I am troubled.  The Advent message was founded on the<br>
understanding of two great institutions established by God at the creation<br>
of the earth: (1) the Sabbath and (2) marriage between a man and a woman. <br>
These two institutions are at the core, the bottom line, of our faith and our<br>
hope. <br>
<p>
Adventists believe that Satan has been actively seeking to obliterate the<br>
meaning and importance of the Sabbath institution.  We also believe he has<br>
been seeking to do the same to the heaven-ordained union between husband<br>
and wife.  Satan's work ***does*** involve perversions and corruptions of<br>
a heterosexual nature, but it does ***definitely*** also involve<br>
homosexuality, the Satanic counterfeit of God's perfect plan.<br>
<p>
Homosexuality is, in my view, not defendable from Scripture, and<br>
expositors have to take great liberties with God's Word in their attempts<br>
to defend what God plainly calls sin.   Also, there is a disturbing<br>
attempt to focus ***only*** on God's love, while totally ignoring the very<br>
real attributes of His justice and intolerance for sin.  Yes, God is<br>
unwilling that any should perish, but NO, He will not save people in their<br>
sins.  Individuals who cling to what the Bible and God's Spirit plainly<br>
declare as sin, such as homosexuality, will simply not be "safe" to save.<br>
<p>
The Scriptures are not subject to private interpretation.  God's<br>
Word interprets itself as we compare Scripture with Scripture.  It's very<br>
uplifting for us to dwell on God's great love for humanity (John 3:16),<br>
but we must never lose sight of God's justice, for it is because God is<br>
just that our dear Savior Jesus Christ had to receive the penalty that we<br>
deserved in order to bring salvation to us.  The magnitude of sin is seen<br>
in the torture endured by the spotless Son of God.  <br>
<p>
The same hands that created the Universe were nailed to Golgotha's cross,<br>
as Jesus paid the penalty for all us sinners, including the homosexuals. <br>
Yet if we persist in deliberate and continued sin, we, like they, will be<br>
eternally lost.  God is fair.  He is just.  He is interested in assuring<br>
that when sin is cleansed from the earth, it shall not arise a second<br>
time.  The safety and peace of the Universe will be assured forever.<br>
<p>
We may want to force God's Word to our viewpoint, but it just doesn't<br>
work that way.  We must humble ourselves to that which God has revealed<br>
to us.  Homosexuality is a perversion and a sin, no more and no<br>
less so than heterosexual perversions, and the unrepentant homosexuals,<br>
like all unrepentant sinners, will perish in their sins.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
    <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
