<!-- body="start" -->
Hi Steve Hix,<br>
<p>
I've got some questions.  Do you know of the gun or weapons<br>
magazines at your local news stand?  Have you seen the advertisers<br>
and "do it yourself" tips on "making" your special weapon (usually<br>
not a type of gun for killing animals)?  Can you think of all the people<br>
living in Atlanta, Chicago, or Houston who are hunters (of non-human<br>
animals) and will use their gun for that purpose (often there is more<br>
than one gun owned)?  Obviously "good" gun owners are getting the<br>
pinch because of a few and increasing number of "bad" gun owners.<br>
The NRA did not BUDGE to correct itself until enough concerned<br>
people brought them onto the carpet - so the picture isn't so pretty.<br>
<p>
The problem does seem to be that too many guns are being used<br>
successfully in cases where humans are being killed.  Now those<br>
who advocate gun ownership rights must take responsibility for<br>
reform.  Hopefully the "reform" will be much more than effective<br>
ownership laws (see: my post about root causes).<br>
<p>
However, there are supposedly "believers" in this world, who's lives<br>
and philosophy should make a positive difference in life - correct?<br>
So what might the Church (SDA specifically) do to help curb the rise<br>
in violent crimes in general, and gun-use crimes specifically?<br>
<p>
You did say that you're a member of the NRA?  Maybe you or others<br>
who support gun-ownership, can give tips on what to do and where to<br>
do it.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
