<!-- body="start" -->
Tang Ben,<br>
<p>
A text, OUT OR CONTEXT, is a pretext (LLU religion prof.).  It seems that the<br>
CLOBBER texts are in good use.  Focusing on the argument again.<br>
"Fornicator" or no-fornicator, WE have to answer for our words and deeds,<br>
Tang.  Some people who have studied these self same texts come to a<br>
different conclusion than you do (I'm one).  The Church must answer for its<br>
words and deeds.  If there is difference in interpretating the same <br>
text, and the<br>
Church ignores it or snowballs over it in order to keep its traditions <br>
- the Church<br>
must answer to God.<br>
<p>
In this we know for sure, when we bash from the pulpit or in our homes we<br>
send out a message which manifests itself in words and ways of sin.<br>
This bashing has no less effect on the persons spirit than a pipe, <br>
smashed into<br>
someone's face.  Repeatedly, I've suggested that we turn our eyes back to Jesus<br>
when dealing with this issue.  The reason?  Because we are dealing with real<br>
humans, whom we are tempted to demonize  - and whom we are quite ignorant<br>
about.<br>
<p>
As for Jude 1:7 saying "They committed fornication and followed unnatural<br>
lusts."  Again, granted that homosexual sexual expression is wrong, WHAT<br>
TYPE OF SEXUAL ACT WAS REALLY BEING SOUGHT BY **ALL** THE<br>
MEN OF SODOM WITH **TWO** MEN/ANGELS?  I'm told that the apocryphal<br>
text which Jude seems to be making an allusion to, uses literal Greek phrasing<br>
which anticipates these questions by using words which specify "going after<br>
alien or other or strange flesh".  Homosexual _rape_ is WRONG - yes!<br>
The heterosexual rape which Lot offers as alternative instead was JUST AS<br>
wrong  - at least from what we now know about females being equal humans<br>
too!  The word of God is deeper and richer than we can ever experienced it,<br>
don't be afraid and close your eyes, when you see different things at <br>
different<br>
depths.<br>
<p>
Eze 16:49-50 does show us that sins of Sodom are found everywhere today.<br>
Yet only one gets *legalized* discrimination (granted that homosexual<br>
relationships are a sin), or the wrath of religious fundamentalists.  <br>
There are<br>
more "abominations" discussed in scripture, than "homosexuality" (granted<br>
that our knowledge of sexuality and gender status has grown no farther than<br>
their was then).  "Lying lips" are one of them.  If we neglect to tell <br>
the whole truth<br>
especially when there is opportunity to learn the whole truth of the <br>
matter, we lie.<br>
This is why the Church should deal with this issue a little less pompously.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Yes, and besides helping tham materially, we need to help them as</i><br>
<i>&gt;homosexuals, to change their lifestyle of sin; but some of them don't want</i><br>
<i>&gt;this type of help although they need it.</i><br>
<p>
Even if a homosexual needs to change her/his orientation or stop being<br>
sexual with another homosexual, the church has skipped step 1 for step 2.<br>
Jesus shows us by example, how to relate to people... human need first,<br>
spiritual need second, never letting the two cancel out each other.  We still<br>
have practical business to take care of at "step 1".  This is what the <br>
discussion<br>
on SDAnet should be about.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Well, i don't know how we can think that we know less. It seems self-evident</i><br>
<i>&gt;to me at least, that homosexual liaisons are included in the abominable sins</i><br>
<i>&gt;of Sodom. The bible is unclear on matter matters, but it condemns</i><br>
<i>&gt;homosexuality in no uncertain terms. There's no two ways about it, its an</i><br>
<i>&gt;abomination, a sin.</i><br>
<p>
Again, this is your opinion.  You still must deal with the real humans, <br>
and lives<br>
when you finish reciting text.  But be sure you're informed when <br>
speaking a "true"<br>
witness to, for, about or against your neighbor.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
