Since this topic has come up again on SDAnet, I'd like to make<br>
some comments about the incidents at Waco.  These comments are<br>
all supported by at least 2 or 3 sources.  Apparently the<br>
tanks with battering rams damaged the stairwells of the<br>
complex, making it difficult to get from place to place.<br>
Also, according to people who escaped, the tanks started the<br>
fire by knocking over several lanterns.  In addition, the<br>
holes punched by the tanks in the walls of the complex<br>
helped to fan the flames, as reported by the government<br>
inquiry.  In addition, the tear gas used will not spontaneously<br>
ignite but will burn if it comes in contact with open flame.<br>
So it seems quite possible that the FBI agents (unintentionally)<br>
made it hard for the people to escape, then started, fanned,<br>
and fueled the fire.<br>
<p>
As for their reasons for going in, it's possible that the<br>
stress of being under surveillance accentuated the wierd<br>
tendencies of the group.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
