<title>May_1993: RE: Biases</title>
<h1>RE: Biases</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 May 93 02:52:42 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#285">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#285">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#285">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#285">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0286.html">Steven Timm: "New journal: Adventist Today"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0284.html">Woody Baker: "RE: Bible and Homosexuality"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I did not say in this instance, that _you_, Steve Timm, have raped the Bible.<br>
What I said was, "I along with many others, do not say that the Bible is<br>
irrelevant in the area of human relations.  To the contrary, the Bible has<br>
beautiful EVERLASTING __principles__ for human relationships.<br>
The problem is not a silence on this matter, but a RAPING of the Bible by<br>
**those who for centuries, have interpreted it to fit their bigotry and <br>
prejudice**."<br>
<p>
The key phrase is those who interpret scripture to fit their bigotry and<br>
prejudice.  Interpreting scripture out of context, or without the whole<br>
background information.  If "those" means Marcus Stringer, then I am living<br>
outside of the principles and character of Jesus Christ.  The Jewish nation in<br>
Jesus' day don't own the market on this.  This is something which we all must<br>
be careful about.<br>
<p>
Heterosexuality = the physical, mental, emotional, spiritual attraction to a<br>
person of the opposite gender.  Homosexuality = the physical, mental,<br>
emotional, spiritual attraction to a person of the same gender.  Scientific<br>
study shows that this happens.  The belief that what has been toted to<br>
be fact about homosexuality, may not actually be the whole story, is the<br>
beginning.  Anyone might come to that cognitive dissonance either by being<br>
a homosexual, or having a friend or loved one who is a homosexual.<br>
This relationship will play a part in the need to know about it, as the <br>
fear and<br>
ignorance of the same might play a part in a need NOT to know or the<br>
need to refute alternative thought about it.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Do you think that all that has to be done is to explain away the few texts</i><br>
<i>&gt;that are usually used, and then say "because it is not prohibited, it is OK?"</i><br>
<p>
No, I believe that what needs to be done is a careful, full context study<br>
of scripture on any issue - currently focussing on the homosexuality issue.<br>
Getting informed through scripture should not be divorced from being<br>
informed through knowing the reality of the actual human needs and<br>
experiences.  Christ has already exemplified how to do this.  I must<br>
advertise the book "The Desire of Ages", it is a most invaluable gift<br>
from God to us.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Part of the reason I feel the way I do is that I know of no case personally</i><br>
<i>&gt;where a gay person really is happy and gay.  If the proponents were pointing</i><br>
<i>&gt;to happy families with dad and dad and two kids or mom and mom and kids</i><br>
<i>&gt;it would be different.</i><br>
<p>
I know of "happy" couples, some of them are Seventh-day Adventist.<br>
Granted that they aren't so happen when they are disfellowshiped,<br>
denied employment or housing, when their son or daughter gets in trouble<br>
at school, when one is in the hospital and the other is being refused <br>
visitation<br>
or when they're being "demonized" by people who have no real knowledge<br>
of who they are.  Essentially they are no more or less, "happy" than we'd<br>
expect heterosexuals to be in those same situations.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;All the personal cases I know and all the statistics</i><br>
<i>&gt;I hear suggest that homosexuality is a high-risk behavior in which</i><br>
<i>&gt;monogamy is rare.  For that matter, if the bible allows homosexuality,</i><br>
<i>&gt;why worry about monogamy, because polygamy is known and permitted</i><br>
<i>&gt;in the Bible?</i><br>
<p>
This was the same for me until I read more books, and met more people.<br>
I think that a lot of behavior which is attributed to homosexuality or the<br>
homosexual "lifestyle", is not of homosexuality at all, rather it is <br>
sludge from<br>
being "cast out" of society for millennia.  Homosexuals have been denied the<br>
opportunity to live "in the day", as it were.  Then the "moralists" go <br>
into the<br>
"night" to point the finger.  However, they are not pointing at a <br>
problem, but to<br>
the problems fruit or "run off". Don't bother trying to imagine Christ <br>
in this picture,<br>
I've tried.  He and the principles of His character are nowhere to be found.<br>
The problem, is that humans have been oppressed without us knowing the full<br>
truth or because we'd rather _not_ know it  I'd not be good in supporting<br>
polygamy (at least for myself) because of my concept of my preferred type of<br>
relationship.  "One on one" is difficult enough.  However, I'd speak <br>
out if they<br>
were being denied their human rights as Christ acknowledged them.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
