<!-- body="start" -->
I too read an article several years ago concerning flu and hogs. Most new<br>
virus' originate in southeast asia where aqua farming is predominant. The<br>
article discussed a theory about the origins of these new virus'. Each<br>
family has a pond in which they grow rice. They also raise a couple type<br>
of carp in these ponds. Each pond has a pig pen built over it so that<br>
the pigs may fertilize the pond. The farmers also raise ducks on these same<br>
ponds. Ducks also are carriers of an avian flu virus but as I recall it<br>
doesn't infect pigs. Instead it infects humans. The pig virus' also infects<br>
humans. The humans act as "mixing vessels" for these flu's which may<br>
occasionally invade the same human cell where DNA is mixed. Occasionally<br>
a new viable flu is produced. Viola! A Swine flu or Hong Kong flu.<br>
<p>
Another article discussed research into the spread of flu virus' and how<br>
the correlated to duck migratory patterns. A possible explaination for<br>
the annual flu seasons as the ducks migrate through the area. It also<br>
mentioned how the ponds in northern Canada function as stew pots for<br>
these avian flus.<br>
<p>
Does anyone know if duck is forbidden food?<br>
<p>
Daryl<br>
<p>
Daryl<br>
