<title>May_1993: RE: Gun, Guns</title>
<h1>RE: Gun, Guns</h1>
Woody Baker (<i>woody@knapper.cactus.org</i>)<br>
<i>27 May 93 10:32:46 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#288">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#288">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#288">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#288">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0289.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: SDAs and homosexuality."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0287.html">Daryl Starr: "Re: Pigs and the FLU"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;The basis of American culture, and success is the concept of the free</i><br>
<i>&gt;man, with land.  Our founding fathers adopted the philosphy that the</i><br>
<i>&gt;only way to be truely free, is to be able to hold (own) land, and the</i><br>
<i>&gt;means to defend it.  Guns have been traditionaly, the weapons of</i><br>
<i>&gt;choice.  An armed, freeman is the best insurance against tyranny.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Thus gun ownership is critical to making the US what it is.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Cheers</i><br>
<i>&gt;Woody</i><br>
<p>
I hear this argument all the time.  "The founding fathers said.....",<br>
or "the founding fathers adopted the philosophy that...".   Now I do<br>
believe that the founding fathers did express a great deal of wisdom<br>
in the bill off rights and the constitution.  But this is 1992.<br>
There are some aspects of life that do not apply to modern day<br>
soceity.  The large urban cities with their drug and crime and<br>
poverty did not exist.  We must study present day culture and try to<br>
understand what is needed for this time.<br>
<p>
It reminds me of those in our church will give as a reason for<br>
everything, "Mrs White said..." without taking into consideration the<br>
context, the age in which she wrote, or even the person(s) to who she<br>
was speaking.  Were the founding Fathers inerrant or infallible?<br>
I certainly believe that the document they wrote was one of the best<br>
ever written, But come on now, we have problems that they never<br>
dreamed of, or probably could never have imagined.  That's why there<br>
are amendments to the constitution.<br>
<p>
So long folk,<br>
<p>
Len<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
