<title>May_1993: New journal: Adventist Today</title>
<h1>New journal: Adventist Today</h1>
Harvey Brenneise (<i>brneise@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 May 1993 11:10:57 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#291">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#291">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#291">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#291">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0292.html">Steven Timm: "Communicating at cross purposes:"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0290.html">Bruce Holm: "Homosexuality and the Bible"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some on the net may be aware that a new SDA-related journal has just<br>
been published entitled _Adventist Today_.  I have received 2 copies in<br>
the last few days.  It is published in Loma Linda, and the editor is former<br>
Review editor Raymond Cottrell, now retired.<br>
<p>
The Waco affair is the feature of the first issue.  The articles are as<br>
follows:  <br>
<p>
The Waco Cult &amp; Religion<br>
  Ex-Adventists at Mr. Carmel:  PR Problem or Learning Opportunity?<br>
  History and Fatal Theology of the Branch Davidians<br>
  Interview with Pastor Charlie Liu<br>
  The Waco Syndrome<br>
  David Koresh:  Narcissistic Personality or Dynsfunctional Religious<br>
Leader<br>
  Experiences in Loma Linda<br>
  Koresh on Ellen White<br>
<p>
Report:  LSU and LLU--After the Divorce<br>
<p>
Adventists &amp; Abortion<br>
  Pro-Life and Pro-Choice:  Can the Church Have It Both Ways?<br>
  1992 Annual Council Guidelines<br>
  A Higher Calling<br>
  Myths and Maybes<br>
  Finding a Consensus<br>
<p>
Editorial:  Let Freedom Ring<br>
Guide Editorial:  Inauguration of a President<br>
Perspective:  A Joyful Moan<br>
Mission Statement<br>
<p>
I have not had time yet to read any of it, but it looks worthwhile to<br>
me.  It may well provide an additional useful information source and<br>
discussion forum (when will we start an electronic journal?).  I have no<br>
connection to this publication and hope provision of this information is<br>
not construed as commercial use of the Internet.  The individual<br>
subscription is $18, $12 for students, $29 for institutions (of course,<br>
they always soak us for more!), $10 additional for outside North<br>
America.  The address is Adventist Today, PO Box 1220, Loma Linda, CA<br>
92354-1220.<br>
<p>
In speaking to Roy Branson (editor of _Spectrum_) while he was at the<br>
All Nations Church recently, he indicated that Waco would be a major<br>
topic of the next issue of _Spectrum_.  He also expressed interest in an<br>
article about Adventists and the Internet, including this list.  If<br>
something isn't in the pipeline (and he didn't seem aware that something<br>
was), perhaps we should get something going in his journal or in others<br>
like _Adventist Today_.  I still think we need to "go after" the<br>
official press as well.  If the _Review_ isn't interested, how about the<br>
_Journal of Adventist Education_ or even _Ministry_.  Somehow we need to<br>
get the word out.  Perhaps our time would be better spent that way than<br>
flaming each other on controversial topics about which we will probably<br>
never reach consensus.<br>
<p>
Harvey Brenneise<br>
(brneise@andrews.edu)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
