<!-- body="start" -->
On May 27,  2:52am, Marcus Stringer wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: RE: Biases</i><br>
...<br>
<i>&gt; Homosexuals have been denied the opportunity to live "in the day", as it were.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Then the "moralists" go into the "night" to point the finger.  However, they</i><br>
<i>&gt; are not pointing at a problem, but to the problems fruit or "run off".</i><br>
<p>
I take it you are excluding yourself from the "moralists"?  If a moralist is<br>
someone who has morals, then I guess I am a moralist.  But yet I don't "go into<br>
the night" and point fingers.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Don't bother trying to imagine Christ in this picture,</i><br>
<i>&gt; I've tried.  He and the principles of His character are nowhere to be found.</i><br>
<p>
Are you suggesting that Christ and the principles of His character are no where<br>
to be found?  Have you read the Gospels lately?  Maybe I misunderstood your<br>
statement.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; The problem, is that humans have been oppressed without us knowing the full</i><br>
<i>&gt; truth or because we'd rather _not_ know it  I'd not be good in supporting</i><br>
<i>&gt; polygamy (at least for myself) because of my concept of my preferred type of</i><br>
<i>&gt; relationship.  "One on one" is difficult enough.  However, I'd speak</i><br>
<i>&gt; out if they were being denied their human rights as Christ acknowledged them.</i><br>
<p>
What human rights are homosexuals being denied?  You seem to like to tell us<br>
about how mistreated they are, but the ones that I have seen around here, they<br>
don't seem to be in too bad a shape.  I am not suggesting that some are not, but<br>
what percentage are we talking about here?  How far should we go in fighting for<br>
their rights over someone else's rights.  Many people have their rights<br>
violated.  That doesn't make it right.  But why single out the homosexuals?<br>
 Lets be fighting against all violated human rights.  I get the feeling from<br>
many of them interviewed on TV that they think they deserve a special status in<br>
society.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
