<title>May_1993: Questions Christians have never answered</title>
<h1>Questions Christians have never answered</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 May 1993 20:22:46 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#294">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#294">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#294">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#294">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0295.html">Tony Dyson: "International Date Line"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0293.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: ATF raid at Waco"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I posted a query to alt.atheism earlier this week asking atheists for <br>
questions that they often ask Christians but had never gotten satisfactory<br>
answers to.  I received about 30 responses so far.  I had not intended<br>
to post them to SDAnet, I had intended to use them as discussion fodder<br>
in our local "Twentysomething" group this Friday night.  <br>
<p>
But a day after I post the query, the boss of "20something" decided to <br>
override my program choice and so now I am left with a bunch of atheists<br>
thumping whatever it is atheists thump instead of the Bible, waiting <br>
for answers.  A likely story, huh?!<br>
<p>
So, in due time, once I get them compiled, I will send them out to SDAnet,<br>
especially since Tammy Healy put me on the spot and told all of them <br>
that I was going to do it.  Some of them are questions that Christians<br>
can debate among themselves for hours at a time.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
