<title>May_1993: RE: SDAs and homosexuality.</title>
<h1>RE: SDAs and homosexuality.</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 May 93 20:34:11 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#302">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#302">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#302">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#302">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0303.html">Steven Timm: "RE: Biases and Perversion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0301.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Biases and Perversion"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On May 27, 10:26am, Marcus Stringer wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: RE: SDAs and homosexuality.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I'm an Adventist, grew up in an Adventist home, but the belief that</i><br>
<i>&gt; homosexuality _in and of itself_, being the work of Satan to destroy</i><br>
<i>&gt; heterosexuality, is not a part of my belief.  Neither is a person's ethnicity,</i><br>
<i>&gt; or physical disability being God's manifest displeasure on that person or the</i><br>
<i>&gt; person's parents.</i><br>
<p>
Anything, if it is not of God, is of the devil.  There is no gray area in life.<br>
 If you agree that homosexuality is not of God, then it by default is from<br>
Satan.<br>
Also worthy of note is that Satan is a master at mixing truth with error.  That<br>
is why so many people fall for what appears to be non-harmful.<br>
<p>
I believe that the practice of homosexuality is a choice...not the tendency but<br>
the practice.  That is quite different from a physical dissability or your<br>
ethnic race, which you do not chose.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; As I've said to others on the net, granted that homosexuality is a sin, we as</i><br>
<i>&gt; professed followers of Christ are a part of this world.  If people are</i><br>
<i>&gt; being killed,</i><br>
<i>&gt; fired, or made homeless because of their homosexuality, and we remain silent,</i><br>
<i>&gt; we commit sin.  To we who know to do good AND DO IT NOT, to us it is sin.</i><br>
<p>
People being killed or fired from, I can't do alot about.  The homeless, yes, we<br>
can do something about that, and should, even to homosexuals.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; &gt;Homosexuality is, in my view, not defendable from Scripture, and</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;expositors have to take great liberties with God's Word in their attempts</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;to defend what God plainly calls sin.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; This is good, it is your view which you are entitled to.  But you/we are NOT</i><br>
<i>&gt; entitled to make a club out of scripture, to beat over people's head *without*</i><br>
<i>&gt; you/us knowing the full reality of the situation, _That_ is what I'm saying to</i><br>
<i>&gt; SDAnet.</i><br>
<p>
Who is beating whom?<br>
<p>
What does the "reality of any situation" got to do with the truth of the Bible.<br>
 If God calls something perverse and sin, what does that got to do with a<br>
situation?  Situations do not affect God' laws, which stand forever.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; As I've said before, Text - Context = Pretext.  The Son of God came eating and</i><br>
<i>&gt; drinking with publicans and "sinners" too.  God's justice is</i><br>
<i>&gt; everlasting, and it takes</i><br>
<i>&gt; into consideration, the WHOLE picture, which we cannot, or will to not see.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Thanks be to Christ, who endured bashing, "demonization", and death for ALL,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and who is returning in terrible justice against the same.</i><br>
<p>
Was Jesus "bashing" Satan when he was tempted by Satan in the wilderness?  Satan<br>
"quoted" scriptures that were distorted interpretations of truth.  Jesus<br>
responded by correctly quoting and representing what was really meant by Satans<br>
statements.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
