<title>May_1993: RE: SDAs and homosexuality.</title>
<h1>RE: SDAs and homosexuality.</h1>
Noe Torres | ECISD (<i>noe@tenet.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 May 1993 20:41:37 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#296">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#296">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#296">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#296">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0297.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "RE: Biases and Perversion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0295.html">Tony Dyson: "International Date Line"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0289.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: SDAs and homosexuality."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Thu, 27 May 1993, Marcus Stringer wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Marriage, a symbol of a covenant should not be</i><br>
<i>&gt; separated from the true meaning it was meant to reflect - God covenanting,</i><br>
<i>&gt; committing Himself to humans</i><br>
<p>
In other words, the God-ordained matrimony between a man and a woman is<br>
"spiritualized" into just a "covenant" into which homosexuals may also<br>
enter.  It doesn't matter if it's man with man, woman with woman,<br>
whatever... anything goes...<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I'm an Adventist, grew up in an Adventist home, but the belief that </i><br>
<i>&gt; homosexuality _in and of itself_, being the work of Satan to destroy</i><br>
<i>&gt; heterosexuality, is not a part of my belief.</i><br>
<p>
As I took pains to point out in my original post, I do not believe that<br>
homosexuality _in and of itself_ is any greater or lesser of a sin than any<br>
other sexually-immoral behavior.  Such immorality, whether hetero or homo,  is<br>
serving Satan's purposes in eroding God's plan for strong family units<br>
centered around the faithful, committed marriage of a man to a woman.  <br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Neither is a person's ethnicity, or physical disability</i><br>
<i>&gt; being God's manifest displeasure on that person or the person's parents. </i><br>
<p>
A person's ethnicity or physical disability does not constitute willful<br>
and deliberate sinning against God's revealed Word.  Homosexual behavior<br>
does.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Nor is the view that the earth is the center of the Universe, a part of</i><br>
<i>&gt; what I believe.</i><br>
<p>
The earth ***is*** the center of the Universe, figuratively speaking, in<br>
terms of where the great controversy is being played out.  And yes, the<br>
great controversy still pits the sophistries of Satan, of which I<br>
believe homosexuality is a part, and the truth and justice of Jesus Christ.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; So neither you nor I can speak for ALL Adventists.</i><br>
<p>
Nor do I wish to.  I express my view of Scripture as I see it just as<br>
freely as you or any other person can.  I am using my KJV to batter no<br>
one.  The rights that you demand you must in turn grant to others on the<br>
net.  <br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I interpret your phrase "taking great liberties" to mean that I take</i><br>
<i>&gt; liberty the invitation to prayerfully "dig in" in search</i><br>
<i>&gt; of the "hidden pearls" in scripture (in context), free from pre-imposed </i><br>
<i>&gt; prejudiced opinion.</i><br>
<p>
No, you interpret it incorrectly.  What I meant by taking great liberties<br>
is to regard plain facts of Scripture as "pre-imposed prejudiced opinion"<br>
because they don't square with what ***you*** believe.<br>
<p>
And finally, Marcuss, you seem to feel that my previous post was a direct<br>
response to you when it was not.  I had no particular person or post in<br>
mind when I wrote it; neither did I even have your name in mind at all at<br>
any point as I composed it.  However, apparently it had an impact....<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
