<i>&gt;I'm confused.  Where have we gone, but in seeking practical application of</i><br>
<i>&gt;scripture - in context - and applying the principles to our lives as </i><br>
<i>&gt;exemplified</i><br>
<i>&gt;by Jesus in His life and teachings?</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Marcus</i><br>
<p>
In seeking goal for personal behavior, it must be remembered that Jesus<br>
did not commit the sins of the various people who followed him.  So<br>
though Jesus associated with prostitutes, tax collectors, and Pharisees,<br>
he did not practice prostitution, nor cheat people on taxes, nor was<br>
he a hypocrite.  Would Jesus associate with homosexuals today?  Certainly.<br>
This does not mean that He would condone such behavior.<br>
<p>
All the various texts in the Bible that can be used against homosexuality<br>
have already been posted once or twice by now.  Marcus and others have<br>
claimed they have explained them all away.  Bible thumping or squirming<br>
away from Bible thumping is going to get us nowhere now.  SDAnet is not <br>
for rehashing of the same arguments that appear everywhere else.  Unless<br>
people on both sides admit the prejudices they come to the Bible with,<br>
it's pointless to discuss the Bible and homosexuality further.<br>
<p>
I must admit that Marcus' method of applying scripture escapes me entirely,<br>
and a few words on his method would be very enlightening.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
