Len,<br>
	You only have to look to China (remember Beijing?), Russia, <br>
Hitlers Germany, the 1200's etc to realize that an unarmed citizenry<br>
has no freedom or control over it's destiny.  It is at the mercy of the<br>
government.  The right to bear arms was specificaly included to prevent<br>
that kind of abuse.  The armed free man is and always has been the only<br>
guarantee of freedom, and the only thing standing in the way of tyranny.<br>
Unfortuanatly, our *dear* U.S. government has worked hard to disarm it's<br>
citizens, basically by guaranteeing that it can out gun them.  Personal<br>
opinion is that all people should be REQUIRED to own a gun, and preferably<br>
a machine gun.  That has been the practice in of the Swiss for many years.<br>
All military aged males have to maintain a gun, and I believe that they<br>
are fully automtic.  Violent crime is almost unknown there.  Soft crimes<br>
however, are rampant (pornography &amp; drugs (which are legal, easily available<br>
and the needles are free, while resulting in a major drug addiction problem,<br>
at least there it trims the drug related crime rate WAY down.)<br>
<p>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
