To Linda Carpenter,<br>
<p>
Just a comment Linda, The former African American that was president of<br>
the North American Division is quoted as saying in so many words, "Why<br>
are Adventists upset about Celebration churches, the blacks have been<br>
doing church that way for many years!"<br>
<p>
Just in response to your comment on interracial marriages, I have had<br>
quite a few such couples as I have pastored in SDA churches. The problem<br>
seems to be that some African Americans as well as whites will not accept<br>
them. I knew of such a couple at Benton Harbor, MI. The white SDA church<br>
would not accept them and perhaps might not have been willing to have<br>
their membership in the church, not sure about that, the black church<br>
really did not accept them either but did tolerate them. This was back in<br>
the 70s. The other thing is that their children had a rough time being<br>
accepted by their peers. Do you think this has changed here in the 90s?<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul Gates&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
