<title>Apr_1992: Good news and happy things</title>
<h1>Good news and happy things</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu,  9 Apr 1992 12:30:48 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#5">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#5">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#5">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#5">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0006.html">Scott Mattes: "Just questions"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0004.html">Steven Timm: "Re: South African Votes &amp; SDA Race Relations"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0012.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Evangelism in Russia"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
It seems like we've been having a lot of muckraking on SDAnet recently,<br>
and I have done some myself.  I would like to start a new thread on positive<br>
developments, things that have been good news for the church in the past <br>
few years.  I'd like to see people post on why they are happy being <br>
Seventh-day Adventists.  Eventually this will lead to a discussion of <br>
the many ways in which the SDA way is the better way to live.<br>
<p>
Momentous developments in the last few years:<br>
<p>
1)  The opening of the Eastern bloc to the gospel as a whole.<br>
2)  The integration of the S. African church<br>
3)  The opening of Adventist World Radio's big shortwave stations.<br>
4)  Election of R. Folkenberg as GC president<br>
<p>
<p>
You get the idea.  Let's let April be a time for optimism and praise <br>
on SDAnet.  I can think of more, but I want to hear from others.<br>
Some people say "no news is good news, therefore good news is no news"<br>
I'd like to dispel that myth this month.  God is leading in such miraculous<br>
ways it would be a shame not to acknowledge it.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
