<title>Apr_1992: What does it mean to die to self?</title>
<h1>What does it mean to die to self?</h1>
David Plaisted (<i>plaisted@cs.unc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 9 Apr 92 14:08:59 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#7">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#7">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#7">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#7">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0008.html">Dave Buxton: "Creation - Book list mailed to me by Dr. Harold Coffin"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0006.html">Scott Mattes: "Just questions"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I heard Elizabeth Elliot on Bible Broadcasting Network discuss<br>
this a few months ago.  She gave an interesting definition of<br>
dying to self.  She said it's a willingness to be inconvenienced<br>
for the Lord.  Sometimes it seems easier to make great sacrifices<br>
for the Lord than to be inconvenienced in little things in His<br>
service.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
