<!-- name="Dave Buxton" -->
<!-- email="davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com" -->
<!-- subject="Re: Just questions" -->
<!-- id="9204092128.AA18164@loowit.WR.TEK.COM" -->
<!-- inreplyto="Just questions" -->
<title>Apr_1992: Re: Just questions</title>
<h1>Re: Just questions</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 09 Apr 92 14:28:09 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#10">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#10">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#10">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#10">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0011.html">Scott Mattes: "Re: Just questions"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0009.html">Eric Snyder: "Creationism book list"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0006.html">Scott Mattes: "Just questions"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;   What is the SDA presence in the former USSR?  China?</i><br>
<p>
We have a few retired pastors in our church and a retired dentist who<br>
can afford to travel.  They have made several trips to russia, bringing<br>
back slides and stories of thousands being baptised.<br>
<p>
One problem they ran into on an early trip was running out of Russian<br>
print Bibles.  They scroured the city.  Found a warehouse full owned<br>
by the Baptist church.  They had to pay $4.00 each for several thousand<br>
Bibles that probably cost about $1 or $2 from donated money.  Inside<br>
each Bible, in large print, were the words "Not for sale, a free gift<br>
to the Russian People".<br>
<p>
In English a lot of people have been taught that<br>
  1st Day == Sunday == Lord's day == Sabbath<br>
And a lot of Baptist, Evangelical, etc literature calls upon people<br>
to read their Bibles, keep the Ten Commandments, keep the Sabbath<br>
according to the Bible.  Here people are used to these admonisions<br>
calling them to church on Sunday.  But in Russia there is no word<br>
for Saturday.  Their Saturday is called by a name clearly meaning<br>
Sabbath.  So these people have been reading the new influx of literature<br>
from these churches, some simply verbatim translated by talented<br>
Russians, and are flocking to what ever churches they can find open<br>
on the Sabbath.  Guess what churches they are flocking to?  You guessed<br>
it.  No wonder the thousands who are eager to baptised as<br>
Seventh-Day-Adventists.<br>
<p>
I also understand that the Mormon church is planning to send thousands<br>
of bicycles and young missionaries to Russia quite soon, perhaps even<br>
as we speak.<br>
<p>
Dave<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
