Dave likes a church where lay men exercise their gifts.  I do too.  But we<br>
also need to think of the churches where the lay ladies lead out, and do<br>
so quite credibly.  I'm sure Dave did not mean to limit the lay persons<br>
to those of the masculine gender.  However, we some times fail to see how<br>
much lay ladies do for churches.<br>
<p>
By the way, what did you think of the special Review issue on women?<br>
<p>
Nancy V.<br>
