Dave, Believe you are right. If the laymen are active, you are going to<br>
have an active progressive church body. If I am pastoring a church and the<br>
laity are not doing anything and if I cannot challenge them -- I am gone!<br>
Time is too short for it to be wasted on people who will not get the<br>
picture. You may be giving a little distorted pix by indicating the laity<br>
are active and it is the pastor that is sitting on dead center! Sometimes<br>
that is true but not as much as churches where laity think they are doing<br>
the Pastor a big favor by attending church for 2 1/2 hrs on Saturday.<br>
<p>
Paul<br>
