<title>Apr_1992: Re: After Death - Soul/Spirit</title>
<h1>Re: After Death - Soul/Spirit</h1>
Dave (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 17 Apr 1992 12:11:37 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#32">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#32">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#32">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#32">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0033.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Scott Mattes: "Re: More Good News and Happy Things"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0028.html">Eric Snyder: "After Death - Soul/Spirit"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0037.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: After Death - Soul/Spirit"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some time ago I put together a series of posts for s.r.c. on the<br>
topics of what happens after death.  In the process I collected<br>
about 600 relevent texts which included the texts favored by those<br>
who wish to prove immortal souls etc.  I also have a collection<br>
of quotes for Bible dictionaries and such that show that Bible<br>
scholars who are trying to write objective analyses of what the<br>
Hebrew and Greek really mean -- that these people have documented<br>
the truths of Adventism on these topics of souls, spirits, . . . .<br>
<p>
Anyway, I did post my series to SDAnet as well.  I recieved a lot<br>
of positive feedback from s.r.c. people.  I received a few positive<br>
notes from SDAnet people and lots of flack from SDAneters who felt<br>
it was consuming their valuable time.  So, I won't re-post the material,<br>
it is rather exhaustive for those who simply want one or two proof<br>
texts.  But if anyone would like copies I can email to you.  Here are the<br>
topics I developed and posted:<br>
<p>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-0 - INTRODUCTION<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-1 - HISTORY<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-2 - SOULS in the GRAVE<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-3 - OUT OF BODY EXPERIENCES<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-4 - SOUL SLEEP<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-5 - RICH MAN &amp; LAZARUS<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-6 - ASBESTOS WICKED<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-7 - THIEF ON CROSS<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-8 - ESCAPE HATCHES<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-9 - SOUL PRISONS?<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-10 - NOT STRAIGHT TO HEAVEN<br>
   DEATH &amp; HELL-11 - was it SAMUEL who talked to SAUL?<br>
<p>
Several of these deserve to be re-written having read a new book by<br>
a Baptist who does a better job than we do of proving Biblical soul<br>
sleep.  I have two books by men who grew up in the traditional views<br>
of eternal souls and hell fire.  They had independently been<br>
dissappointed that the sermons and books of their churches did not<br>
really offer Biblical analysis, being more inclined to quote Plato<br>
and or Augustine who quotes a lot of Ploto, and of course other<br>
trandition rather than Biblical arguments.  So, each independently<br>
set out to write a book that set asside tradition and really went<br>
at it from the Bible.  Their books ended up sounding like good SDA<br>
books on the state of the dead.  No, their books are more comprehensive<br>
and contain better proofs than the SDA books, to prove the SDA<br>
doctrines.  Very interresting indeed.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<p>
[Dave, I think that if there is a good excerpt in the series on what is <br>
the spirit, it would be very helpful to see that here.  Also I would <br>
be interested to know the names of the books you mention above.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
