Continuing positivity month here on SDAnet:<br>
<p>
Jesus died for you, and for everyone!<br>
He rose again!<br>
He's coming back!<br>
<p>
I saw a variety of different church services this weekend, including a very<br>
powerful drama called "The Choice"<br>
I came to the conclusion that it doesn't hurt one bit to experience some <br>
emotion about Jesus.  They don't call it the Passion play for nothing.<br>
People of that day didn't really understand Christ's mission, and I don't<br>
think that we can claim that we are any better than them.<br>
<p>
The death and resurrection of Christ is not something that can be experienced<br>
only with the head.  It must also be known through the heart and through the <br>
emotions.  I understand it slightly more because I have cried with those <br>
who watched him die, I have cheered at His victory over the grave and <br>
sin and death.  Lord, help us so that our emotions will never become <br>
de-sensitized to this story.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
