<title>Apr_1992: Re:  Home schooling and the Moores</title>
<h1>Re:  Home schooling and the Moores</h1>
Steve Hix (<i>fiddler@dobbs.eng.sun.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 20 Apr 92 13:12:16 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#45">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#45">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#45">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#45">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0046.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: The real good news!"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0044.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Anyone have a bio on EGW?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0036.html">Steven Timm: "Home schooling and the Moores"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
