<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; &gt;Subject: Home schooling and the Moores</i><br>
<p>
We're home-schooling our three.<br>
<p>
While the Moore's have contributed to the design of our<br>
curriculum, and our approach, they are only one of<br>
several sources that we have chosen.<br>
<p>
With the differences in character and personality of<br>
each of our kids, I don't think that any single source<br>
would be a best fit for all children.<br>
<p>
As another poster said; if you're not ready and willing<br>
and able to put in a lot of time and effort, home schooling<br>
probably isn't the way to go.<br>
<p>
But if you can, it can be very rewarding.  I'd have to say that<br>
my wife and children are my very best friends.  The idea that<br>
they'll all to soon be heading off to (probably) academy and<br>
(almost certainly) college is not necessarily good news to all<br>
of us.  (Although I have a lot less trouble with the notion than<br>
does my wife...academy was good for me, she never went, joing the<br>
church about the time she entered college.)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
