Hi Scott, Well, we will probably be with the easter Bunny on Sunday. We<br>
will be celebrating the birthday of one of my granddaughters at her house!<br>
<p>
Tomorrow (Saturday) at our Cambridge church we will be winding up our<br>
50-Day Adventure which actually takes us up to Easter. This year our<br>
subject was on "Being the Kind of Family God Wants Us To Be." We had a<br>
journal for our families that they used during the week. It was really<br>
neat. We discovered the dysfunctions of the family, how it also permeates<br>
into the church and how to overcome them. So tomorrow I will be have my<br>
Easter sermon!!<br>
<p>
BTW one of my soninlaws loaned me a book a few weeks ago. The title is :<br>
"The Subtle power of Spiritual Abuse." Sub-titles : "Recognizing and<br>
Escaping Spiritual manipulation and False Spiritual Authority Within the<br>
Church." The authors are David Johnson &amp; Jeff VanVonderen. It is published<br>
by Bethany House publishers and I would highly recommend it. Very good<br>
sermon material!!<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
