<!-- body="start" -->
The question is -- is it works that save us.<br>
<p>
I think Jesus illustrated it well when He spoke of the true vine and<br>
its branches.  Our works can be like apples on an apple tree.  But<br>
who would care to eat a wax apple that has been tied in place upon<br>
the same apple tree.  Or who would care to eat an apple that has<br>
fallen from the apple tree, to lay upon the ground for a week or two.<br>
<p>
We are saved by our works, but clearly it is the apple tree that<br>
deserves all the credit for growing the apples.  And that apple tree is<br>
Christ Jesus who came to save us from our sins.  He can grow apples,<br>
all we can do is sculpture wax into something that looks like an<br>
apple from a distance.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
