<title>Apr_1992: Moores and Home School</title>
<h1>Moores and Home School</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 21 Apr 92 07:32:25 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#53">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#53">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#53">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#53">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0054.html">Eric Snyder: "Death/Afterlife"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0052.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Tried to get some info on the Moores last night.  But the Moores are<br>
out of town for the week and the employee I know has just moved and<br>
nobody has the new phone number.  So I talked to the mother of a<br>
former employee.<br>
<p>
I don't know how long ago, but Hewitt Foundation was established<br>
largely because of the Moores.  Hewitt was the biggest financial<br>
contributor who made it all possible.<br>
<p>
The Moores have been on the board of directors for years but not<br>
necessarily the president in charge.  A few years ago the elected<br>
president steered a course that the Moores could not go along with<br>
and so resigned.  The Moore Foundation was founded about two or<br>
three years ago.  Phone 206-635-2736<br>
<p>
Hewitt Foundation is more of a correspondance course curricula with<br>
teachers who grade papers.  They also support home schooling.<br>
<p>
The Moore Foundation offers no correspondance school support.  The<br>
sell books and materials.  They have "counselors" in home schooling<br>
but offer NO "teachers" ready and willing to grade papers and serve<br>
up grades and graduation certificates.  It is a much parent oriented<br>
program as opposed to teacher orriented.<br>
<p>
The life blood of Hewitt was the Moores.  Hence Wewitt is drying up<br>
and may soon have to close.  Moore Foundation is growing.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
