<title>Apr_1992: Introducing myself as a new member of SDAnet</title>
<h1>Introducing myself as a new member of SDAnet</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 22 Apr 92 13:04:17 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#71">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#71">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#71">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#71">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0072.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0070.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Thanks to Dave Buxton, I just recently became aware of this moderated<br>
distribution list.  As with other such, it is appropriate that I introduce<br>
myself.  I shall do so from several perspectives, several of which are<br>
in case we may have met before.<br>
<p>
Geographic Bio:  Born in Fredericton, NB, in 1953.  Bangalore, India, 56-60.<br>
Madras, India, 60-62.  Andrews U campus, 62-63.  Calcutta, India, 63-66.<br>
Simpsonville, MD, 66-67.  Oshawa, ON, 67-71.  Sarnia, ON, 71-75.  Lukanga,<br>
Zaire, 75-77.  Waterloo, ON, 77-79.  Minneapolis, MN, area 79-82.<br>
Chandler, AZ, 82-88.  Sherwood, OR, 88-91.  Phoenix, AZ, 91-present.<br>
<p>
Educational Bio:  Home schooled grades 1-3,5,6.  Andrews Elementary for 4th.<br>
Vincent Hill School, India, 6th (part) &amp; 7th.  Atholton, MD, Jr Acad 8th.<br>
Kingsway (College) Academy.  Andrews University, BS Math (except for soph<br>
year in Collonges, France, 72-73).  Univ of Waterloo, MMath in Comp Sci.<br>
<p>
Work Bio:  Trans-Africa Div of SDA, Zaire; Honeywell, Minn; Motorola, AZ;<br>
BiiN, OR; Intel, OR; Motorola, AZ.<br>
<p>
Family Bio:  Parents, Grace &amp; Gerhard Christiansen, now in Willowdale, ON.<br>
Sister Linda.  Got married to Kathie Ewald in 1975.  Children are Liesl, 14,<br>
Weimar Academy (home schooled 1-7, half of 9th); Monique, 11, home school;<br>
Andrew, 4; Bonnie, 1.<br>
<p>
Spiritual Bio:  Born a P.K. into an excellent family.  Fond memories of<br>
family worship, singing around the piano, etc.  Determined I would make P.K.<br>
an honorable phrase.  Helps to have had a father who understood that his<br>
witness is badly damaged if his family suffers from neglect.  Baptized<br>
at age 14 (or was it 15?).  Got pretty cocky in college, figured I'd heard<br>
everything, knew all the stories, knew many "proof texts".  The fall came<br>
when I became unwisely engaged.  Rescued from foolishness and calamity by<br>
God's grace and the effectual, fervent prayers of my parents.  Via Glenn<br>
Coon's ABC's of prayer, recognized there was a whole lot more to spirituality.<br>
Other writers, such as Morris Venden, have helped me see the need for growing<br>
relationship with the Lord.  Motivated to seeking Godly wisdom for *every-<br>
thing* in life by attending Bill Gothard's Life Principles Seminars (basic<br>
and advanced) numerous times, and (finally, after all these years) reading<br>
Conflict of the Ages series and Tho'ts from the Mount of BLessing.<br>
<p>
Service Bio:  Teaching in Cradle Roll, Kindergarten, Primary, Juniors,<br>
Youth, and Adult Sabbath School.  Deacon, Waterloo, ON; Elder, Maple Plain, MN,<br>
Tempe, AZ, Gladstone Park, OR.  Preaching, Waterloo, Maple Plain, various<br>
places in AZ.  Organizing deaf ministries, interpreting in AZ and OR.<br>
Has been a source of joy to see those I taught starting like ministry in<br>
Austin, TX, and continuing and growing greatly in Gladstone, OR.<br>
<p>
Spiritual challenges:  Being laid off from Honeywell; BiiN collapsing,<br>
2nd child becoming profoundly deaf at age 6 months.<br>
<p>
"It will be worth it all, when we see Jesus.<br>
 Life's trials will seem so small, when we see Christ.<br>
 One glimpse of His dear face, all sorrow will erase.<br>
 So bravely run the race, 'til we see Christ."<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola TSD (DW278), 2900 S. Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ  85282
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  For the Lord gives wisdom:  out of His mouth comes knowledge
    and understanding (Prov 2:6).
</pre>
