Hi all,<br>
<p>
	I think the problem here is a slight misunderstanding. Dave<br>
can set me straight if I misunderstood him. I think what Dave was saying<br>
is that we are saved by our works in that without works we can not be saved.<br>
<p>
I like to put it by saying that we are not saved by works but without<br>
works we are not saved. The reason is that the salvation experience produces<br>
works if there are no works we obviously have not received the saving grace.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
