Hello all,<br>
<p>
Cheryl's farewell address, sad as it was, raised several questions<br>
for me about the SDA church.  I belong to an independent, fundamental,<br>
Bible church and have no connection with SDAs except through this<br>
net list (and my oral hygienist).  I want to raise these questions<br>
on the net without directly discussing Cheryl's actions.  I would<br>
contact her directly as she invited, but I don't feel adequate to<br>
express my thoughts and feelings to her in print.<br>
_________________________________________________<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Cheryl writes</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;was born and raised a 4th-generation Adventist, but ...</i><br>
<p>
The Catholic church considers someone a member of the church<br>
due to being born of Catholic parents.  Do SDAs feel the<br>
same?  Can one be born into the SDA church?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I never really understood and may never totally understand </i><br>
<i>&gt;why I had to suffer so much at the hands of the SDA church.  </i><br>
<p>
Did I miss something in her narrative?  After reading it<br>
through several times, I saw no abuse by the SDA church.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;only way for me to be open to believe in God's true church. </i><br>
<i>&gt;...the LDS church</i><br>
<p>
Does the SDA church consider the LDS church a valid member<br>
of the body of Christ?  For that matter, what do you think<br>
about fundamental, Bible churches?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;[I now realize that] I am not a guinea pig down here on </i><br>
<i>&gt;this sinful earth, a victim of the war in heaven.  Rather I </i><br>
<p>
Is this a perception taught by the SDA church?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Cheryl Berthelsen</i><br>
<i>&gt;cberthel@cc.utah.edu</i><br>
<p>
My best regards,<br>
Dan Blake<br>
dblake@hprnd.rose.hp.com<br>
<p>
P.S.  One more question from another posting many moons ago.<br>
Does the SDA church have woman pastors?<br>
