<!-- body="start" -->
It is interresting to note how often Jesus quotes from the Old<br>
Testament.  Consider the following two texts.  The 2nd is what Jesus<br>
said just before he died.  The first is made in a Psalm that really<br>
has nothing to do with death or its immediate anticipation.  And<br>
yet the 2nd is a popular text for "proving" a separable spirit.<br>
<p>
   "Into Your hand I commit my spirit; You have redeemed me, O LORD God of <br>
   truth."  --  Psa 31:5  (NKJ)<br>
<p>
   "And when Jesus had cried out with a loud voice, He said, "Father, 'into <br>
   Your hands I commend My spirit.'" And having said this, He breathed His <br>
   last."  --  Luke 23:46  (NKJ) (See Ps 31:1,5)<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
