<title>Apr_1992: Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works</title>
<h1>Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works</h1>
Gross (<i>grossg@dg-rtp.dg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 28 Apr 92 16:25:17 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#93">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#93">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#93">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#93">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0094.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0092.html">Eric Snyder: "Death/Afterlife"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0089.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
# <br>
# &gt;   At a guess I would say it comes from a fear of the W word (works).<br>
# &gt; People are being taught that they don't have to do anything to be saved.<br>
# &gt; Just a thought.<br>
# &gt; <br>
# &gt; Scott<br>
# <br>
# A non-SDA friend of mine that I see frequently.  He ended up wanting to<br>
# talk about tithing.  He said that his not tithing used to bother him<br>
# enormously but he thanks God that He has delivered him from that<br>
# affliction so that he can now go about with a free conscience over it.<br>
# He anticipates that in His own good time God will make the way possible<br>
# and show him when and how to go about tithing.  "Its in the Lord's<br>
# hands now and so I don't worry about it anymore."<br>
<p>
And people wonder why they don't see God moving in their lives!!<br>
<p>
My take on tithing is pretty simple.  God owns it all.  Ten percent is<br>
the starting point in my giving.  God has given me a job and an<br>
income.  Every penny belongs to Him.  And I recall that when it comes<br>
time to write the check.<br>
<p>
# The Jesus people used to have a saying that goes approximately like<br>
# this:  Turn your life over to Jesus, put yourself in neutral and then<br>
# go have a good time.<br>
<p>
This succinctly sums up "cheap grace."  I would agree with "Turn your<br>
life over to Jesus."  However, I have yet to find works involved with<br>
salvation.  That is, you cannot work and earn salvation.  However, I<br>
do believe that once you have accepted Jesus Christ as your Lord and<br>
Saviour, you will do the works of faith.  If someone says that they<br>
are a Christian but have no works, I think they need to take another<br>
look at their life.  If works are involved in salavation, then it<br>
could be argued that one person worked harder than another and thereby<br>
earns more salvation than another.  It can also be argued that God is<br>
a respecter of persons and can be swayed by His own finite creation.<br>
<p>
Before I close out -- I'd like to find out if anyone out there has any<br>
comments on Luke 18:1-8.  I've been looking at prevailing prayer and<br>
would like additional ideas on this topic.  Thanks.<br>
<p>
En Agape tou Iesous,<br>
<p>
Gene Gross <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
