On Wed, 29 Apr 1992 19:46:39 PST you said:<br>
<i>&gt;I too thank Enoch and Christine for getting this thing started.</i><br>
<i>&gt;I will express my only concern in the form of a wish.....that the</i><br>
<i>&gt;"mail" on this list never be subject to any sort of prior restraint</i><br>
<i>&gt;ie. screening for content prior to posting.  I recall that at least</i><br>
<p>
  SDAnet IS moderated and the contents of each msg are screened before<br>
being sent out to the subscribers.  If deemed not appropreate it is<br>
returned to sender saying why.  I know, several of mine have been so<br>
returned.  Since I know that this will happen it doesn't bother me, but<br>
if I didn't know in advance I would holler.<br>
<p>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<br>
