<title>Apr_1992: Re: After Death - Soul/Spirit</title>
<h1>Re: After Death - Soul/Spirit</h1>
Scott Mattes (<i>COTRSSM@sea04vm.navsea.navy.mil</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 30 Apr 92 11:35:19 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#102">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#102">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#102">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#102">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0103.html">Scott Mattes: "Re: Today in Paradise"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0101.html">Scott Mattes: "Re: Leadership of SDA-L in transition"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
  Looking at my new Strong's I noticed that almost all of the uses of<br>
the word 'spirit' in the NT are the same Greek word.  It is used by<br>
Jesus before he died, when referring to the Holy Ghost, for evil spirits<br>
and good spirits.  Likewise, the OT almost always uses the same word<br>
when speaking of spirits.<br>
<p>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<br>
