<title>Apr_1993: Re: The Sovereignty of God</title>
<h1>Re: The Sovereignty of God</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 6 Apr 93 14:35:29 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#143">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#143">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#143">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#143">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0144.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: The real issues?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0142.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: SDA: advent"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0127.html">Steven Timm: "The Sovereignty of God"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0147.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  The Sovereignty of God"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; In the discussion about the evangelical beliefs a few days ago, Ruben </i><br>
<i>&gt; put in the statement "but God does not reign on earth now..." when</i><br>
<i>&gt; referring to the doctrine of the kingdom of God.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
They said<br>
<p>
Quote<br>
<i>&gt;         cross, His bodily resurrection and His present reign in heaven and</i><br>
<i>&gt;         earth.</i><br>
Unquote<br>
<p>
I said ....<br>
<p>
Quote <br>
	But Jesus doesn't rein on this earth (ecept in our hearts ) that will<br>
	only happen after the 2nd coming the prince of this world is Lucifer, <br>
	thats why suffering and death abounds.<br>
Unquote<br>
<p>
God yes, Jesus no.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I would like to suggest that the prayers of 2000 years of Christians,</i><br>
<i>&gt; "Thy Kingdom come" have not gone unanswered.  Since Christ's death on</i><br>
<i>&gt; the cross, Satan is a defeated foe.  But through all time, before and</i><br>
<i>&gt; after</i><br>
<i>&gt; the cross, God is and has been sovereign on this earth.</i><br>
<p>
What happens then to your interpretation of the Rock and statue<br>
in Daniel 2 ? Jesus is not currently performing His Kingly role in heaven<br>
but rather His priestly role. When He lays off His priestly robes in as <br>
outlined in Rev then it is that He puts on His Kingly robes and Comes as the<br>
King to reclaim the earth.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Now this doesn't mean that we will see a postmillenial style "reign of</i><br>
<i>&gt; peace" on earth like many evangelicals believe.  But we do have the</i><br>
<i>&gt; Kingdom of Grace</i><br>
<i>&gt; here and now and we shouldn't forget it.</i><br>
<p>
When Jesus was asked where the Kingdom of God was to be found He simply said<br>
"The kingdom of God is within you" ! Jesus understood the situation.<br>
<p>
Yes God still holds the reigns but He who comes to receive the dominion and<br>
the power and the glory has not yet arrived. We await that moment. <br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0144.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: The real issues?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0142.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: SDA: advent"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0127.html">Steven Timm: "The Sovereignty of God"</a>
