<title>Apr_1993: The Sovereignty of God</title>
<h1>The Sovereignty of God</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  5 Apr 1993 23:03:47 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#127">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#127">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#127">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#127">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0128.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: The real issue"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0126.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0141.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  The Sovereignty of God"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the discussion about the evangelical beliefs a few days ago, Ruben <br>
put in the statement "but God does not reign on earth now..." when<br>
referring to the doctrine of the kingdom of God.<br>
<p>
I would like to suggest that the prayers of 2000 years of Christians,<br>
"Thy Kingdom come" have not gone unanswered.  Since Christ's death on<br>
the cross, Satan is a defeated foe.  But through all time, before and<br>
after<br>
the cross, God is and has been sovereign on this earth.  Every act on this<br>
earth, good or bad, happens only with His consent.  Any sentence which<br>
begins with the words "God can't...." is by definition false.  (However,<br>
as I write,<br>
I realize there is a counterexample in the Bible.  Can anyone find it?)<br>
<p>
In the Old Testament God takes credit for both good and evil things that <br>
happen.  To ascribe anything less to Him is to strip Him of His omnipotence.<br>
Any power that the devil has is given at the express consent of God.  <br>
<p>
Now this doesn't mean that we will see a postmillenial style "reign of<br>
peace" on earth like many evangelicals believe.  But we do have the<br>
Kingdom of Grace<br>
here and now and we shouldn't forget it.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0128.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: The real issue"</a>
