****This is the Project Gutenberg Newsletter for March, 1993***<br>
Our Goal, To Give Away One Trillion Etexts By December 31, 2001<br>
<p>
*[10,000 titles to 100,000,000 people equals 1,000,000,000,000]<br>
<p>
We now have a volunteer to mail disks!  See below.<br>
You can also contact him through the College address below.<br>
<p>
Note to you interested in NETwork TRAINing and NETTRAIN at end.<br>
<p>
Index to all etexts from 1/1/91 to 3/1/93 included below.  More<br>
of our etexts are available around the networks than we keep on<br>
line at our own location.  We post only the most recent etexts.<br>
<p>
If each book goes to 100 million people by the end of 2001 then<br>
we should be at about 4.0 billion with release of the following<br>
not counting pre-1991 releases:  which are still in the process<br>
of being dug out of our archives, new headers attached, and new<br>
placement in new directories on our new 600M fileserver.  Thank<br>
you NeXT, for loaning us that machine!!!  Thanks also to Apple,<br>
Calera, CTA (TextPert), and Caere.<br>
<p>
Save the instruction below, as some locations have changed!<br>
<p>
The remainder of our responses to your letters are contained in<br>
in the mid-month Newsletter2.<br>
<p>
*This file is about 400 lines in length, and is about 10Kbytes*<br>
Keep this newsletter, it is your "readme" file for the location<br>
of all material currently posted at the University of Illinois,<br>
[mrcnext.cso.uiuc.edu . . . see below details and instructions]<br>
and also contains information on how to retrieve our books from<br>
East Coast, Central and West Coast locations and email and BBS.<br>
[Try The Bitter Butter Better BBS, (503)-620-0307]<br>
Some of our etexts are available via the Cleveland Freenet.<br>
You can call via modem at 1-216-368-3888.<br>
