point 3 is the stickiest.  Internet access or at least uucp can be had<br>
reasonably cheaply, or free.  The well charges $15.00 per month, plus<br>
$2.00 per hour connect time to a direct internet feed, with ftp, etc etc<br>
available.  A uucp connection should be free.  Several of our colleges<br>
are on internet. any of them could make a uucp connection available to the<br>
CG.  The GC would poll the site, and thus THEY would pay for the connection.<br>
It would really be no skin off any of the universities/colleges that are<br>
hooked up to provide a uucp account.  I think that what I would recommend<br>
is that the GC use a machine (a pc, or some other unix box) to handle uucp<br>
and then re-distribute it internally over the internal network that they<br>
run.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
