<title>Apr_1993: What is AntiChrist ?</title>
<h1>What is AntiChrist ?</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 29 Mar 93 16:03:49 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#6">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#6">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#6">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#6">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0007.html">Steven Timm: "Re: SDAnet mail"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Steven Timm: "RE: Why the SDA church needs conservatives"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0014.html">Malcolm Butler: "Re: What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi all,<br>
<p>
Just a question for us to consider. What does the AntiChrist mean to you ?<br>
<p>
Just to get you going, here is my definition.<br>
<p>
First of all we know that the AntiChrist is not someone who is openly<br>
antagonistic to Jesus and Christianity because thats what the word means :<br>
<p>
Lets see, Liddel &amp; Scotts "Greek - English Lexicon" says regarding<br>
the prefix "anti" as used in compound words such as "antiChrist" that<br>
it can have 7 meanings.<br>
<p>
1. over against<br>
2. in opposition to<br>
3. one against another<br>
4. in return<br>
5. instead of<br>
6. like<br>
7. corresponding<br>
<p>
Now W.E.Vine in his book "An Expositional Dictionary of New Testament Words"<br>
says regarding the word "antichristos"<br>
<p>
	"Can mean either against Christ or instead of Christ, or perhaps<br>
combining the two, one who assuming the guise of Christ opposes Christ,"<br>
(Westcott)"<br>
<p>
So we see that the antichrist apart from Satan as numero uno, and a certain<br>
owner of the 666 number as numero dos, it can also mean<br>
all those things which profess to be Christian but in effect are impostors<br>
of the real thing, surplanting it. In this way all false doctrines are of <br>
antichrist all false ministers are of antichrist, and should I say it much<br>
music that purports to be Christian but in reality isn't is also of antichrist.<br>
This definition would but naturally also include such things as the Apocripha,<br>
and any other forms of distortions of the truth.<br>
<p>
In fact the prefered location of antichrist and things of that spirit are<br>
naturally to be found, not outside of the church but within it, because <br>
that is the only way it can hope to "assuming the guise of Christiantiy <br>
opposes Christianity" so don't go looking ofr antichrist among the Satanists<br>
cause he won't be there.<br>
<p>
Q. where did the numero dos antichrist set up his throne, was it not on the<br>
very front pew of the church ?<br>
<p>
Anyway after considering all of that, how many of you consider that the <br>
antichrist is alive and well and working today in every congregation ?<br>
Or do we think that because we are SDAs we are magically excluded from<br>
his artifacts ?<br>
<p>
<p>
So hows that ? <br>
<p>
Of course now its over to all of you to show me how wrong I am. :^)<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
