[From Drew Corrigan]<br>
<p>
Hi All,<br>
<p>
A friend of mine recommended I find and read the book,<br>
  "Seeking a Sanctuary"<br>
by Lockhart and Bull, published by Harper&amp;Row.<br>
<p>
The book is a discussion on changes in the SDA church over the years,<br>
but my (and my friend's) interest is how these changes have presaged<br>
similiar changes in the WCoG over more recent times.<br>
<p>
Has anyone read this book, and if so, what were your impressions?<br>
<p>
Thanks,<br>
<p>
Drew.<br>
<p>
[I read and enjoyed the book.  I would recommend it to any friend who is <br>
interested in an objective view of SDA's. Unfortunately, I believe <br>
it is now out of print.  SCT]<br>
