<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Timm:<br>
<i>&gt;One of the chief problems that we face in the church today is that people</i><br>
<i>&gt;relate to God exactly like they relate to their father, and both </i><br>
relationships<br>
<i>&gt;are dysfunctional.</i><br>
<p>
	Did someone say DYSFUNCTIONAL?  The human child-father<br>
	relationship is dysfunctional?  This is just short of stepping on the<br>
	toes of some cherished culture/role traditions - not unrelated to the<br>
	cultural war going on around us.  (Those family relations classes<br>
	at Southern College _are_ paying off.)  I've always thought that<br>
	humans would have to be delivered from much of our human<br>
	relational baggage, in order for Christ's work to be completed in<br>
	the earth.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
