<title>Apr_1993: Re: Info (fwd)</title>
<h1>Re: Info (fwd)</h1>
Alan Fargusson (<i>70751.2436@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>30 Mar 93 11:30:23 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#28">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#28">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#28">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#28">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0029.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Religious liberty? and Branch Davidians"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0027.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Seeking a Sanctuary"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In this area the lowest cost Internet connection (E-mail and news only) is<br>
$75/month.  FTP access would cost another $100/month.  I know because CUC has<br>
looked for lower cost connections.  This service would probably not support a<br>
PC since they only know UNIX.  I suspect that there is nobody at the GC that<br>
knows how to keep a UNIX system running.  In fact I am almost positive since I<br>
know people that have done PC support over there.<br>
<p>
I think that CUC would be willing to help the GC, but we are limited by the<br>
complete lack of an equipment budget.  Currently we only have one working<br>
modem, which of course is very busy.  To be fair to the students we would have<br>
to ask for monetary support.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
