<title>Apr_1993: Those three angels</title>
<h1>Those three angels</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>30 Mar 1993 13:50:54 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#8">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#8">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#8">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#8">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0009.html">Harvey Brenneise: "SDA--Spectrum"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0007.html">Steven Timm: "Re: SDAnet mail"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0011.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Those three angels"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Here's a question which has occurred to me of late. I'd be interested to <br>
hear your responses to this.<br>
<p>
Christians have a clear divine mandate to share the gospel. This can be<br>
seen in the gospels alone, by the fact that Christ directed his disciples<br>
to visit towns &amp; villages etc, and of course there is also the great<br>
commission. <br>
<p>
Reading Revelation, I find three angels flying over the Earth, crying with<br>
a loud voice "Fear God &amp; give glory to him" and so on. <br>
<p>
Historically, SDAs have felt called to "preach the three angels' messages"<br>
as an important part of their mission. In fact, in many cases it seems that<br>
this has eclipsed even the preaching of the gospel. One of the things the<br>
ultra-conservatives like to do here in Australia is to use the three-angels<br>
logo on all their advertisements and correspondence, partly as a protest<br>
over the organization's choice to use a more modernistic/abstract logo.<br>
(I don't know whether that new logo is worldwide or not).<br>
<p>
Anyway, my question is this: Christians are definitely called to preach the<br>
gospel. Is there a similar mandate for "preaching the three angels' messages"?<br>
Why do we feel the need to pass those messages along for the angels? Have<br>
we been asked to do so, or do we see those three angels as purely figurative,<br>
and hence unable to actually cry "Babylon is fallen" and so on?<br>
<p>
This is not meant to be an attack on any given point of view, I am just<br>
interested in the Biblical mandate for that task which SDAs have considered<br>
their own.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<p>
(whoops...forgot to put SDA in the subject line...too late now!)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
