<title>Apr_1993: Re: What is AntiChrist ?</title>
<h1>Re: What is AntiChrist ?</h1>
Malcolm Butler (<i>malb@boojum.ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 30 Mar 93 14:40:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#14">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#14">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#14">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#14">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0015.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Things"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0013.html">Steven Timm: "RE:  Maxwell's letter"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0006.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0041.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Ruben Gonzalez writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;So we see that the antichrist apart from Satan as numero uno, and a certain</i><br>
<i>&gt;owner of the 666 number as numero dos, it can also mean</i><br>
<i>&gt;all those things which profess to be Christian but in effect are impostors</i><br>
<i>&gt;of the real thing, surplanting it. In this way all false doctrines are of </i><br>
<i>&gt;antichrist all false ministers are of antichrist, and should I say it much</i><br>
<i>&gt;music that purports to be Christian but in reality isn't is also of antichrist.</i><br>
<i>&gt;This definition would but naturally also include such things as the Apocripha,</i><br>
<i>&gt;and any other forms of distortions of the truth.</i><br>
<p>
As far as it goes, this is a reasonable way to define that which is<br>
antichrist.  But does it help us to identify it?  After all, when it<br>
comes down to the crunch, even the biblical canon was defined by men,<br>
not by God.  Luther, for instance, was not comfortable with the book of<br>
James being in the Bible.  I'm not claiming that Luther is right about<br>
everything he taught.  Does that make him the antichrist, though?  How<br>
"wrong" can someone be before they qualify as the antichrist?<br>
<p>
A loose definition like this makes it easy to call anything we disagree<br>
with the antichrist.<br>
<p>
<p>
Malcolm<br>
<pre>
-- 
Switched Networks Research Centre,               malb@ee.uts.edu.au
Uni. of Technology, Sydney, Australia            +61 2 330 2344
</pre>
