<title>Apr_1993: SDA: Lukewarm worshippers</title>
<h1>SDA: Lukewarm worshippers</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 30 Mar 1993 23:11:02 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#19">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#19">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#19">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#19">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0020.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: 3 angels"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0018.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Seeking a Sanctuary"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0016.html">Steven Timm: "Why the SDA Church needs Lukewarm Couch Potatoes"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0055.html">Fred Christiansen: "re: SDA: Lukewarm worshippers"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; [Third in a series of why the SDA church eventually needs everyone.  SCT]</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 1)  We need someone on which to lay the guilt trip  "You may not be doing </i><br>
<i>&gt; anything else, but at least you can give us money and soothe your</i><br>
<i>&gt; conscience.  Guilt-ridden people like this have provided major funding</i><br>
<i>&gt; for ministries in which I have been involved.  I need one of these right</i><br>
<i>&gt; now.  Give me a call.:-)</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 2)  We need lots of lukewarm people in the church so we can cherish the </i><br>
<i>&gt; "Laodicea" image as part of our self-image as a church.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 3)  We need people to fill the pews to make it look like lots of people </i><br>
<i>&gt; are coming to church.  It'd be real empty otherwise.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 4)  We need people to boost the membership count so we can get an</i><br>
<i>&gt; assistant pastor again.  If they're paying tithe, so much the better.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Steve Timm</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
------------<br>
I am forced to believe this is tongue-in-cheek humor.  That bothers<br>
me for a couple of reasons.<br>
<p>
1.  First of all, I see nothing humorous about the subject of luke-<br>
warm worshippers; Jesus made some extremely serious statements about<br>
them (Rev. 3:16-18).  You may as well joke about the lost.<br>
<p>
2.  Being that we have lost some subscribers due to the volume of<br>
messages, empty messages such as these may just be the straw that<br>
breaks the camel's back.<br>
<p>
3.  T-in-C humor is usually made by people who, in some small way,<br>
believe what they are saying.<br>
<p>
The stated conclusion is wrong: the church does not need lukewarm<br>
worshippers and is better off without them (1John 2:19).<br>
<p>
Dan Blake<br>
<p>
P.S.  Steve, don't forget your own request that net-traffic subject<br>
lines begin with SDA:.  You are going to have to lead by example if<br>
you hope to get general compliance.<br>
<p>
[It was not my request.  I oppose this idea and have no plans to start.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
