<title>Apr_1993: Re: 3 angels</title>
<h1>Re: 3 angels</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 30 Mar 1993 23:43:52 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#30">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#30">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#30">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#30">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Marcus Stringer: "SDAnet - RE:  Maxwell's letter"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0029.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Religious liberty? and Branch Davidians"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;Paul claimed to be preaching the gospel, in fact, the *only* gospel, yet he</i><br>
<i>&gt;had no knowledge of the three angels' messages, at least he didn't refer to</i><br>
<i>&gt;them. I have heard people say that they believe the three angels' messages</i><br>
<i>&gt;are part of the gospel, but I'm not sure that I feel comfortable with that</i><br>
<i>&gt;in the light of what Paul had to say. I'm just not sure whether we're not</i><br>
<i>&gt;redefining "gospel" to suit our own understanding of what the people should</i><br>
<i>&gt;hear.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Tony</i><br>
<p>
Our calling in life is to love God supremely and our neighbors as ourselves.<br>
The sad fact of human existence is that sin keeps us from doing this in our <br>
own strength.  The good news of the gospel is that God offers<br>
forgiveness for our failings in this regard and restoration to full and<br>
complete relationships.  <br>
<p>
It's my firm belief that no part of the Adventist message is dispensable<br>
if the full restoration promised by the gospel is to be achieved.  Proving <br>
that statement could well be a life's work.  So instead, I ask, what do you <br>
think exists in the three angels message that could be dispensed with and <br>
still preach "the full gospel".  What about church doctrines in general?<br>
On the contrary, is there anything in the full gospel that is missing<br>
from the "three angels message" or the larger SDA message as a whole?<br>
<p>
Getting people to just "be saved" and proceed to store their generic and<br>
dysfunctional relationship with God in their filing cabinet, with no<br>
effect on their lives, is not the gospel to me.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
