One point about the 3-angels messages and our uderstanding of Daniel<br>
Revelation prophecies:<br>
<p>
Without this understanding the Ecumenical Movement would certainly have<br>
its appeal.  Hey, UNITY, who can argue with that theme?  Instead we<br>
see this movement for what it is and have to pull back.  Even go the<br>
other way to remain pure on what the Bible and SOP have taught us.<br>
Ecumenical membership requires that no member church preach any sermons<br>
against what another member church's theology.  Whats left is the<br>
"love" gospel.  Now of course there is nothing wrong with preaching<br>
about love, especially Agape.  Certainly!  But what about the texts<br>
that speak of "all scripture" and the "meat".  Is pablum Christianity<br>
all that is allowable for Unities sake?  NO, all scripture is meat<br>
for study.  Without the 3-angels messages, how would we know that?<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
