<title>Apr_1993: SDA: That original subject line</title>
<h1>SDA: That original subject line</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>31 Mar 1993 09:35:52 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#21">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#21">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#21">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#21">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Maxwell's letter"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0020.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: 3 angels"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In defense of myself...I did in fact censor that subject line before sending<br>
that post in. The original foul language present there was not my own, and I<br>
deliberately tried to remove the offensive content without obscuring what the<br>
original poster had written there.<br>
<p>
I should also state categorically that the post did *not* reflect my personal<br>
beliefs about creation, evolution, or the appropriate way to discuss either.<br>
Apart from the subject line, it did however seem to me to accurately represent<br>
some of the views held by scientists in the general community. Many people in<br>
the Christian church are not exposed to either the negative views or the<br>
contrary evidence, and a lot of those people will never read talk.origins.<br>
Heck, *I* don't even read it, I was just looking through the list of newsgroups,came across it and thought I might have a quick look. There was so much <br>
trash there that I won't be wasting the time to look there again, but I <br>
thought I might share that one post with all of you guys.<br>
<p>
If anyone felt that it was "gutter level", then I apologize for sending it. I<br>
myself didn't get that impression, maybe it was just due to the fact that I<br>
had just finished looking at some that definitely were down there. I wasn't<br>
trying to start an argument, either, just to add a perspective probably not<br>
held by *anyone* on SDAnet.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
