Paul claimed to be preaching the gospel, in fact, the *only* gospel, yet he<br>
had no knowledge of the three angels' messages, at least he didn't refer to<br>
them. I have heard people say that they believe the three angels' messages<br>
are part of the gospel, but I'm not sure that I feel comfortable with that<br>
in the light of what Paul had to say. I'm just not sure whether we're not<br>
redefining "gospel" to suit our own understanding of what the people should<br>
hear.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
