<title>Apr_1993: Re: What is AntiChrist ?</title>
<h1>Re: What is AntiChrist ?</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 31 Mar 93 10:58:54 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#41">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#41">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#41">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#41">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0042.html">Bruce Holm: "RE:  Maxwell's letter"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0040.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: SDA: Maxwell"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0006.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0062.html">Steven Timm: "Re: What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Mar 29,  4:03pm, Ruben Gonzalez wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: What is AntiChrist ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; ...</i><br>
<i>&gt; Just a question for us to consider. What does the AntiChrist mean to you ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; ...</i><br>
<i>&gt; First of all we know that the AntiChrist is not someone who is openly</i><br>
<i>&gt; antagonistic to Jesus and Christianity because thats what the word means :</i><br>
<p>
I don't follow your logic here...why does it follow that AntiChrist means not openly<br>
antagonistic to Christ?  To me, to be against someone is very likely to mean<br>
antagonism towards that person.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; So we see that the antichrist apart from Satan as numero uno, and a certain</i><br>
<i>&gt; owner of the 666 number as numero dos, it can also mean</i><br>
<i>&gt; all those things which profess to be Christian but in effect are impostors</i><br>
<i>&gt; of the real thing, surplanting it. In this way all false doctrines are of</i><br>
<i>&gt; antichrist all false ministers are of antichrist, and should I say it much</i><br>
<i>&gt; music that purports to be Christian but in reality isn't is also of antichrist.</i><br>
<i>&gt; This definition would but naturally also include such things as the Apocripha,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and any other forms of distortions of the truth.</i><br>
<p>
As Malcolm stated, where do you draw the line as to what is truth and what isn't?<br>
 Who decides what Christian music is truth and which isn't?  What if the music<br>
doesn't even have lyrics?  I think it dangerous to go around labeling this and that<br>
the antiChrist because you interpret (thats what it comes down to doesn't it?) them<br>
as not truth.  I believe that truth and light from God are revealed in varying<br>
degrees to every individual, as they are able to handle it.  Could not a situation<br>
then arise where what was revealed as truth to one person has not been revealed to<br>
the other person, therefore according to your definition of the AntiChrist, the list<br>
of what is AntiChrist varies from person to person.  I don't believe this is what the<br>
Bible speaks of as "the" AntiChrist of the last days that will come and deceive many.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; In fact the prefered location of antichrist and things of that spirit are</i><br>
<i>&gt; naturally to be found, not outside of the church but within it, because</i><br>
<i>&gt; that is the only way it can hope to "assuming the guise of Christiantiy</i><br>
<i>&gt; opposes Christianity" so don't go looking ofr antichrist among the Satanists</i><br>
<i>&gt; cause he won't be there.</i><br>
<i>&gt; ...</i><br>
<i>&gt; Anyway after considering all of that, how many of you consider that the</i><br>
<i>&gt; antichrist is alive and well and working today in every congregation ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; Or do we think that because we are SDAs we are magically excluded from</i><br>
<i>&gt; his artifacts ?</i><br>
<p>
I see a difference between "the" antiChrist and being antiChrist.  I would place<br>
your description somewhere in the second catagory.  The first refers to a specific<br>
single entity or person, not a dynamically changing list of things as the second<br>
catagory implies.  We as SDAs are not magically excluded from anything.  We all face<br>
the same temtations and trials that everyone else does, as did Jesus while on this<br>
earth.  But I can't say what or who the antiChrist is or when it will appear or if it<br>
has or hasn't appeared yet.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Bruce G. Holm               503-685-1350      email:  bruceh@wv.mentorg.com
Mentor Graphics Corp.       503-685-7000
8005 SW Boeckman Rd.
Wilsonville, OR 97070-7777     Disclaimer:  Opinions expressed are my own!
</pre>
