<h1>Re: Why the SDA Church needs Lukewarm Couch Potatoes</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 31 Mar 93 12:29:33 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#56">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#56">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#56">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#56">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0057.html">Steven Timm: "SDA: Landmarks"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0055.html">Fred Christiansen: "re: SDA: Lukewarm worshippers"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0024.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Why the SDA Church needs Lukewarm Couch Potatoes"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Marcuss wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Here's an idea!</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Let's make a more descriptive gage:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;&gt;GAGE&lt;&lt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; Conservatively conservative</i><br>
<i>&gt; Moderately conservative</i><br>
<i>&gt; Liberally conservative</i><br>
<i>&gt; Conservatively moderate</i><br>
<i>&gt; Moderately moderate</i><br>
<i>&gt; Liberally moderate</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; So forth and so on...  = )</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
One of the big problems we have when we give a label to an individual is<br>
when he has ideas that are considered liberal and conservative.  Marcuss<br>
seems to point out this problem in his Gage. <br>
<p>
IT would depend on who you asked whether someone was liberal or conservative.<br>
I know some people who would consider me too liberal.  I know others who<br>
consider me too conservative.  We might want to more precisely define such<br>
terms. <br>
<p>
I have read books by Adventists who would be considered conservative wanting<br>
a change in the church's interpretation of the seals and the trumpets.  I<br>
have also read articles by Adventists who would be conseidered liberal <br>
wanting the same thing.  Sometimes espousing the same interpretation.<br>
Labels are helpfull to a certain point in defining ideas, but they break<br>
down rather easily, as Marcuss shows.<br>
<p>
What the church needs is people with a pure heart and a love for truth.  This<br>
person will be considered liberal by some and conservative by others.<br>
<pre>
-- 
"Competition is the law of the jungle,
 Cooperation is the law of civilization." - Eldridge Cleaver
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
