[From Harvey Brenneise]<br>
While at the General Conference last week, I picked up the following<br>
list of e-mail numbers in paper and on disc.  I'll try loading this into<br>
this message and sending it out.  If it works, the credit is due to Dan<br>
Bidwell.  I can't discern the organizing principle of the first part of<br>
the list.  It certainly wouldn't win any awards for reference materials!<br>
I hope someday we can maintain a more complete list of this type in an<br>
electronic form.  These addresses all appear to be ATT-Mail, and of<br>
course do not include the many Internet and other addresses that are out<br>
there, particularly in the educational institutions.  For ATT-Mail, give<br>
the user id followed by @attmail.com.  I hope this is useful.<br>
<p>
Harvey Brenneise<br>
Head Reference Librarian<br>
Andrews University<br>
(brneise@andrews.edu)<br>
