<!-- body="start" -->
Regarding the "Evangelical Declaration of Belief," I found very<br>
interesting that the eleven doctrinal points listed are very "generic,"<br>
allowing for wide latitude in interpretation/application.    For instance,<br>
the "indwelling of the Holy Spirit... producing in [believers] an<br>
increasing likeness to Christ...." could safely cover everything from<br>
speaking in unknown tongues to ???   <br>
<p>
The doctrine of "the one holy universal church" is also fascinating,<br>
especially when viewed from an SDA standpoint.<br>
<p>
Several of the eleven declarations closely mirror similar statements in<br>
our own 27 points.  <br>
<p>
I don't think there is much at first glance that is strikingly<br>
objectionable about the evangelical beliefs.  Ruben asks if all the<br>
evangelicals who believe these 11 points will be saved; Luckily, God<br>
hasn't left that decision up to me....   <br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
