I found very interesting Harvey's comments about the general lack of knowledge<br>
about the Internet on the part of GC "men."  This corresponds with what I<br>
have seen in the past ten years among SDAs in general -- that is, either a<br>
distrust in or a lack of committment toward new computer technologies. <br>
When computers are used, the expectation seems to be that they will simply<br>
"automate" function(s) currently being carried out by human beings.  In my<br>
opinion, our denomination is lagging far behind in technological areas<br>
such as computer telecommunications.  And, when I've approached individual<br>
administrators about the problem, I've been met with indifference.<br>
<p>
Have those of you on SDANet had similar experiences?<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
