You can get a connection to the well for a lot less up front fee.<br>
I think it is  $15.00 + $2.00 per hour via telnet.  Full FTP etc.<br>
I find having a simple uucp mail feed, and news reader is quite satisfactory.<br>
If I need something via FTP it is harder to get, but you can go through a mail<br>
server.  UUPC (the uucp port for the PC, is a very stable, smooth program<br>
coming in both DOS and OS/2 flavors.  A 286 with a 20 meg hd or 40 meg hd<br>
is a very cheap commodity (used) currently, and will work admirably<br>
Cheers<br>
