<title>Apr_1993: Re: To be or not to be. (cont)</title>
<h1>Re: To be or not to be. (cont)</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 1 Apr 93 11:51:51 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#72">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#72">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#72">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#72">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0073.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: To be or not to be. (cont)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0071.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  To be or not to be. (cont)"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0044.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "To be or not to be. (cont)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0073.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: To be or not to be. (cont)"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Apr 1, 11:48am, Ruben Gonzalez wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: To be or not to be. (cont)</i><br>
<i>&gt; Hi again,</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; Now that you have all had an opportunity to ponder the practice</i><br>
<i>&gt; questions, here is the real thing.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; Are SDAs evangelical, without knowing it ?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; Should we all just be Seventh Day Baptists ?</i><br>
<p>
<p>
God never said that if you become a Seventh-day Adventist (or a Seventh-day<br>
Baptist, or a ...) and you will be saved.  No, He said Believe on ME and you<br>
will be saved.  I really don't think it really matters what "label" or "brand"<br>
of church you call yourself (as far as salvation goes), what counts it that you<br>
believe on the Lord Jesus Christ and follow His leading and study His word and<br>
spend time with Him in prayer, then God will show you what is truth for you and<br>
show you where changes need to take place in your life.  I realize that this may<br>
sound simplistic but I think that is the bottom line.<br>
<p>
So does it really matter if SDA beliefs overlap other churchs beliefs?  I think it<br>
great that there are other flavors of churches out there that have beliefs that are<br>
close to our own...that means they are that much closer to the truth as we know it.<br>
<p>
If God is truely leading in people's lives, don't you think He will lead them into<br>
what He thinks is truth and important for their lives?<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
