Ruben Writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Hi again,</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Now that you have all had an opportunity to ponder the practice</i><br>
<i>&gt; questions, here is the real thing.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Are SDAs evangelical, without knowing it ?</i><br>
	Some of us are, some of us aint.<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Should we all just be Seventh Day Baptists ?</i><br>
	NO!<br>
	They don't accept Christ's special message to the last day church,<br>
	the Spirit of Prophecy.<br>
<p>
	They dont't accept The work of Christ in the Sanctuary above and<br>
	the human Sanctuary on earth.<br>
<p>
	They don't accept Christ's special message of health.<br>
<p>
	I guess I should change my NO.  If you feel that the SDB church<br>
	is closer to the truth.  Go on.  Was this meant to remain unaswered?<br>
<p>
Let us not fear to hold some of the beliefs that some<br>
evangelicals  hold.  Also let us not fear to  hold some beliefs that they<br>
do not hold, or may even find heretical.  Let us seek to follow truth<br>
whoever may agree or disagree.<br>
<p>
One time I was in a discussion.  I agreed with someone who I usually<br>
did not.  One of my friends told me you need o to really think when You<br>
agree with that person.  My reesponse was, "If the Devil himself<br>
came  here and said that commiting adultury<br>
is wrong I would agree with him."<br>
<p>
Let us stand up for truth.  Some will agree some will not.  In fact, some<br>
will say it is conservative, some will say it is liberal.<br>
<p>
bye<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"Competition is the law of the jungle.
 Cooperation is the law of civilization."  -  Eldridge Cleaver
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
