Well I didn't see anything wrong with what was there (although I am a bit<br>
uncomfortable about the universal church bit).  I am not sure if this is a<br>
reflection of the typical SDA as I have only been an SDA for a few years. <br>
I am also unsure what problem might exist if these were a typical SDA<br>
UNLESS this was a reflection of the only things that they see as truths<br>
emminating from the scriptures.  The items that bring me into conflict<br>
with evangelicals (state of the dead, fate of the wicked, the judgment,<br>
the Sabbath and the moral law, etc.) are important also.<br>
<p>
Ian.<br>
