[From Sherman Cox]<br>
The other day I was reading in Counsels to Writers and Editors.  <br>
<p>
People were attacking Jones and Waggoner saying they were attacking<br>
the landmarks of the church.  Ellen White made an interesting statement.<br>
<p>
She said the landmarks of the church were:<br>
<p>
	1. Sabbath<br>
	2. Snactuary<br>
	3. Law of God<br>
	4. Noinmortality of the wicked.<br>
<p>
	I formget the order it was in.  She said beside these she could think<br>
	of no other.<br>
