<title>Apr_1993: Re: What is AntiChrist ?</title>
<h1>Re: What is AntiChrist ?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu,  1 Apr 1993 22:07:21 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#62">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#62">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#62">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#62">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0063.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  To be or not to be"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0061.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: To be or not to be"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0006.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0108.html">Malcolm Butler: "Re: What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[A friendly reminder to all.  Please cut down on the included text, and <br>
try not to send text wider than 80 columns.  This post from Ruben Gonzalez.<br>
SCT]<br>
<i>&gt; &gt; First of all we know that the AntiChrist is not someone who is openly</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; antagonistic to Jesus and Christianity because thats what the word means :</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I don't follow your logic here...why does it follow that AntiChrist</i><br>
means not openly<br>
<i>&gt; antagonistic to Christ?  To me, to be against someone is very likely to mean</i><br>
<i>&gt; antagonism towards that person.</i><br>
<p>
The operative word is "openly"<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; As Malcolm stated, where do you draw the line as to what is truth and</i><br>
what isn't?<br>
<p>
Well I always thought that God's Word was the test of truth.<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; [...]</i><br>
<i>&gt; then arise where what was revealed as truth to one person has not been</i><br>
revealed to<br>
<i>&gt; the other person, therefore according to your definition of the</i><br>
AntiChrist, the list<br>
<i>&gt; of what is AntiChrist varies from person to person. </i><br>
<p>
<p>
No, I'd didn't say that, you have "interpreted that" I did not give any method<br>
for detecting AntiChrist, except as it is revealed in scripture.<br>
<p>
However spiritual discernment in accordance with scripture does vary from<br>
person to person, this doesn't mean different things are AntiChrist, or that<br>
AntiChrist "Dynamically varies" it means some may perceive it while others <br>
don't.<br>
<p>
In fact I actually liked Marcuss' understanding of the matter.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; [...]</i><br>
<i>&gt; earth.  But I can't say what or who the antiChrist is or when it will</i><br>
appear or if it<br>
<i>&gt; has or hasn't appeared yet.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
But I can because the scripture tells me how to identify the AntiChrist quite<br>
clearly. <br>
<p>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
