<title>Apr_1993: Re:  To be or not to be</title>
<h1>Re:  To be or not to be</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 1 Apr 93 23:33:16 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#63">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#63">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#63">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#63">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0064.html">Bill Allen: "SDA: Kushner: To Life"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0062.html">Steven Timm: "Re: What is AntiChrist ?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0058.html">Malachi Robertson: "To be or not to be"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0075.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: To be or not to be"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;What follows is a Doctrinal Basis of Evangelical Belief.  It is a summary of </i><br>
<i>&gt;the Christian faith, and is used by Christian Unions which are affiliated</i><br>
<i>&gt;to the Universities' and Colleges' Christian Fellowship (U.C.C.F.), which is</i><br>
<i>&gt;the United Kindom affiliate of the International Fellowship of Evangelical</i><br>
<i>&gt;Students (I.F.E.S.).</i><br>
<p>
Well, i am a member of the Varsity Christian Fellowship, which is affliated<br>
to IFES, so i've seen this list of beliefs before. I must say that i agree<br>
with all of it, and am glad that there are still many Christians who hold<br>
these beliefs, in this day and age, when all sorts of ridiculous (for want<br>
of a better word) ideas are being taught as the doctrines of God.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;No here comes the tricky bit. </i><br>
<p>
Where?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Does this sound any different from your average SDA these days ? Yes or no. </i><br>
<p>
Well, i hope the average SDA these days, or any days, for that matter,<br>
believes all of these teachings, for the are sound Christrian principles,<br>
from God's own word. Of course, the SDA church has a more in-depth body of<br>
knowledge on many biblical teachings, our understanding of the relationship<br>
between the law, sin, grace, faith, salvation, the ministry of Christ and<br>
other things is much richer and clearer and makes a lot more sense than what<br>
a lot of other people have. As such, SDAs can more fully appreciate the<br>
beauty and trueness of these truths.<br>
	As such, i would hope that the average SDA holds all the beliefs in<br>
the Evengelical list at least as strongly, if not more so, than most of the<br>
other churches.<br>
	I don't mean to sound arrogant or boastful (though i know it sounds<br>
that way) but that is what i think.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Is anything wrong with it ? yes or no. (if yes what)</i><br>
<p>
Well, i can't think of anything wrong with it, though i tried.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Will all the evangelicals who believe the above be saved ? Yes or No (why)</i><br>
<p>
Who knows. People are not saved by professing a creed alone. God is merciful<br>
and righteous, and he will judge each individual according to the light he<br>
has been given, and at the end of the day, it is God who saves us all, after<br>
all. God knows his own.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
