<title>Apr_1993: Re: SDA: America</title>
<h1>Re: SDA: America</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 2 Apr 93 9:34:33 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#110">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#110">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#110">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#110">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0109.html">Steven Timm: "No SDAnet messages on Sabbath."</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0106.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0107.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "The Generation That Forgot God."</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Noe wrote<br>
 <br>
<i>&gt; Interestingly, I read an article yesterday from a recent issue of Time</i><br>
<i>&gt; magazine, which describes many of the emergency governance plans that the</i><br>
<i>&gt; U.S. had prepared in case of a nuclear strike by the former Soviet Union. </i><br>
<i>&gt; The plans called for measures that severely curtailed many of our</i><br>
<i>&gt; dearly-held constitutional rights.  To me, the article was a striking</i><br>
<i>&gt; reminder, despite the apparently solidity of our governmental</i><br>
<i>&gt; institutions and our freedoms, of how precarious our rights as</i><br>
<i>&gt; American citizens really are.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I have read such articles  also, but I have also read about actions taken by <br>
the US government to systematically destroy groups not only during war but<br>
during times of peace.<br>
<p>
An example is the American Civil Rights Movement.  This movement was bugged, <br>
brought in on false charges until individualsran out of money for bail, and<br>
rivalries were stirred up between the groups.  This was all done under a<br>
program called COINTELPRO.  This was the FBI's program.  Even the peace<br>
loving Dr. Martin Luther King was not immune to these tactics.<br>
If any one wants  documentation for  these charges e-mail me for I do not<br>
think this is the place to talk any more about  this.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; In a time of "national emergency," the lamb becomes a dragon in a matter</i><br>
<i>&gt; of hours and a "lifeboat" mentality kicks in.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
It is good that you put "national emergency" in quotes, for any time can  be<br>
a national emergency and it can occur during times of peace even to peace<br>
loving groups.  As for America talking like a dragon, she has done  so in<br>
the past, ask blacks and Native Americans.  She will do so again, ask SDAs.<br>
<p>
I do not want to sound anti-american, for our standardof living is great.   Oourfreedoms are definitely higher  than the vast amount of the world.  Some would<br>
say it is the highest, but let us not fool ourselves.  If you make the wrong<br>
people mad, for whatever reason, you can have major problems.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"Competition is the law of the jungle.
 Cooperation is the law of civilization."  -  Eldridge Cleaver
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
