<title>Apr_1993: who does baptism preparation</title>
<h1>who does baptism preparation</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 2 Apr 93 15:02:48 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#102">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#102">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#102">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#102">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0103.html">Malcolm Butler: "Re: Sin and the leading of the Holy Spirit"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0101.html">Paul Gates: "Re:  To be or not to be. (cont)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
While doing some painting recently, I was chatting with a fellow church<br>
member whose son was until recently in my Jr SS class.  I complimented him<br>
on having a son who seemed tho'tful and genuinely interested in<br>
spiritual things.  The father then replied that the son really wanted<br>
to be baptized but they had as yet been unable to schedule something<br>
with the Pastor.  I recommended that they just get lessons from the ABC<br>
and do it themselves (Deu 6:7, 11:19; cf Ex 12:26, Deu 6:20, Josh 4:6,21).<br>
The surprised father said, "You mean I could?"  Absolutely!<br>
<p>
I'd like to highly recommend, from the joys we have experienced in our<br>
family, to take every opportunity possible to bring the things of God<br>
into conversation with your children.  Be alert to occasions when such<br>
can be woven ever so naturally into the fabric of life's circumstances.<br>
To see God's hand in nature, to see His hand in their lives.  To depend upon<br>
His promises, to experience His peace in the midst of a storm, to grasp<br>
His hand in faith when logic would suggest otherwise (Heb 11:6).  And, yes,<br>
in giving the heart to God, accepting Christ as Savior and Lord, and<br>
inviting the in-dwelling Holy Spirit.  And, certainly, in preparing for<br>
baptism, the public commitment to follow Jesus as our Example in everything.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
