<title>Apr_1993: Dillema... What to do in this situation!</title>
<h1>Dillema... What to do in this situation!</h1>
Ademir P. Soares (<i>OPAPS@nasagiss.giss.nasa.gov</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 04 Apr 93 13:37:39 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#140">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#140">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#140">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#140">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0141.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  The Sovereignty of God"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0139.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: The real issues?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0137.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Dillema... What to do in this situation!"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi Steve,<br>
<p>
I received the following letter from a very close friend of mine, from our<br>
church, she is a real good Christian trying to do her best, but now she is<br>
experiencing a terrible dillema.<br>
I'd like to get your input in the following matter, and so from the others<br>
NETER's as well. Please distribute this letter to the Board and to the NET<br>
if u think it could be helpful.<br>
Thanks in advance.<br>
<p>
Yours in Christ.<br>
<p>
Ademir P. Soares<br>
<p>
==-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-<br>
Dear ....<br>
<p>
My problem is as follows:<br>
<p>
I have a nine years old daughter who is beeing influenced by her father ((my<br>
X-husband) who is not SDA). We have been divorced for 6 years. Recently (the<br>
past 6-7 months) he has shown interest in seeing her regularly (one day and<br>
one night a week). He is very materialistic and as such has projected this<br>
type of life style to her. She is very impressed with his way of life (fancy<br>
cars, fancy clothers, jewelry, gambling, his business that is an elegant restau<br>
rant). Now , I have reason for concern he has asked her to live with him. He is<br>
trying all in his power to eliminate all the Christian influence in her life.<br>
She has shown some interest because she will be exposed to this type of life on<br>
a regular basis, and she sees that he wants to take her away from her SDA<br>
family, school, church and friends. However she says that she will not be taken<br>
away from GOD. (I said the same thing when I was 19 and I still went and<br>
married him, later learning the hard way). I have been advised by a good<br>
Christian friend to move out of state with my new SDA husband of three years,<br>
her and our 1 year son. I am not one to run away from my problems but I do NOT<br>
 want to lose my daughter to the world. What should I do?<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
