<!-- body="start" -->
Ruben,<br>
Assuming you are in general agreement with Larson's theological views --<br>
some of which I consider to be marginal-- are you also in agreement with<br>
his methods of being openly critical and denunciatory toward the<br>
denomination?  I really object to a person or a small subgroup within the<br>
SDA church claiming that it has become the repositor for "historic<br>
Adventist doctrine" and that it has a special mandate to carry forth the<br>
torch that the denomination fumbled back then (whenever).  I think such<br>
groups are a few steps away from joining the compound in Waco.  Further,<br>
many of their accusations against the denomination, such as misuse of<br>
tithe money, seem rather pompous and presumptous to me.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
<p>
<p>
