<title>Apr_1993: Re: SDA: America</title>
<h1>Re: SDA: America</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>05 Apr 1993 09:35:46 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#117">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#117">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#117">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#117">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0118.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0116.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Theories of inspiration"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0079.html">Sherman Cox: "SDA: America"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0118.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
It's been years since I heard a sermon on America in prophecy. A sermon<br>
on any Western power would be lost on most audiences in Papua New Guinea<br>
too, I might add! (Although things have definitely changed there since I<br>
left in 1979!)<br>
<p>
I was commenting more on the Ayatollah's labelling the USa<br>
(whoops - hit enter instead of shift)<br>
as "The Great Satan" than anything else. America, being the largest<br>
Western democracy, is seen by many as the epitome of capitalism, self-<br>
interest and greed. For instance, during the gulf conflict I heard many<br>
Australians voice the opinion that if it wasn't for the gulf oil, the U.S.A.<br>
would never have been bothered getting involved. Instead, they decided that<br>
they needed to defend the oil, and started making all these speeches about<br>
freedom and human rights.<br>
<p>
Also, you have to understand what an influence American media exports have<br>
on many other societies. Here in Australia a large proportion of our TV<br>
programming and almost all our movies come from America. If a person sees<br>
the degradation of society as being moved along by TV and film...then <br>
America is often where the finger is pointed. American language, dress,<br>
habits and attitudes are starting to spread through many societies, kind<br>
of like a twentieth century Hellenization.<br>
<p>
So the SDA prophetic understanding regarding America is very easy to believe.<br>
Even now, American public figures are far more likely to stand up and claim<br>
"God's will" for themselves than any other public/political individuals in<br>
the world, excepting probably the pope. So any church/state unification or<br>
religiously-motivated legislation is far more likely to happen there than,<br>
say, Australia.<br>
<p>
This probably hasn't been particularly pleasant reading if you are a<br>
patriotic American. Please believe me when I say that what I have written<br>
refers to America the entity, not to Americans as individuals! <br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<p>
ps An example of one particularly unpleasant American public figure is<br>
   Billy Ray Cyrus, who seems to be able to say God, America and Me in every<br>
   second or third sentence!  "Ah just thank Gahd for helping Billyray<br>
   Cahrus reach his dream. That's what America is all about" and so on.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
