<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;&gt; means nothing to a tribesman who doesn't do so anyway?  Is the SDA church </i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt; American no matter what country we are in?  SCT]</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
Well, i don't know about other countries, but here in Southeast Asia, there<br>
is a lot of American influence in the church, especially in Singapore, where<br>
the Far Eastern Division HQ and the Southeast Asia Union HQ are based (there<br>
are a lot of Americans working in the administration in these places) and we<br>
often get GC people passing through and they more or less always give a<br>
sermon in my church; and there are choirs and evangelists which sometimes<br>
pass through these parts too. My church pastor is presently an American from<br>
Texas and there are many American expatriates in the congregation too.<br>
Besides that, some of our publications: quarterlies, Adventist Review NAD<br>
edition, books etc. come from the USA, (but we now get Signs of the Times<br>
from Australia too, and that edition is somewhat different from the US<br>
version). The Southeast Asia Union College here in Singapore, where our<br>
local pastors are trained, follows the American system of education and is<br>
affliated to Walla Walla College, and many Southeast-Asians who graduate<br>
from it go on to study in the States and return more Americanised. So yes,<br>
the flavour is somewhat American.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I would also like to hear about the teaching of USA in prophecy in other </i><br>
<i>&gt;countries.  Please people outside of the USA give the sermons and theology</i><br>
<i>&gt;taught in your country.</i><br>
<p>
Well, as far back as i can remember, our teachings about the USA in prophecy<br>
have been similar to those found in "The Great Controversy" by E. G. White<br>
and "Daniel and the Revelation" by Uriah Smith. That is that the Lamb-Like<br>
Beast of Revelation 13 represents America, and in the light of events in the<br>
past couple of years, it appears that this prophecy is coming true even now.<br>
<p>
-Beng Tang,  National University of Singapore<br>
