<title>Apr_1993: Re: The real issues?</title>
<h1>Re: The real issues?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 5 Apr 93 18:26:06 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#139">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#139">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#139">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#139">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0140.html">Ademir P. Soares: "Dillema... What to do in this situation!"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0138.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: SDA: America"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0104.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "The real issues?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Noe Torres | ECISD writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; I received in the mail today an unsolicited pamphlet from Dr. Ralph Larson of</i><br>
<i>&gt; the independent ministry known as "Steps to Life." </i><br>
<p>
Steps to Life printed it; however, I believe Ralph Larson is not on the staff.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I'm wondering how many of you on SDANet have read this publication and what</i><br>
<i>&gt; your thoughts on it are?</i><br>
<p>
I've read it.  The response from Hartland by Colin Standish comes across<br>
"kinder and gentler" but expresses similar concern over historic beliefs.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Specifically, how do you feel about Larson's charge that the following five</i><br>
<i>&gt; "historic Adventist doctrines" are being "replaced" by Calvinistic teachings:</i><br>
   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^<br>
Whether his claims ("charge" feels over strong to me) are valid or not<br>
would come from examining the large body of extant material.  He claims to<br>
have collated the relevant and supporting material into a couple of his books.<br>
A reading of these or the original documents might prove enlightening.<br>
My wife and I are studying Scripture and SoP again with an eye to some of<br>
these points.  As to whether Larson should speak up wherein he sees a<br>
concern .. we have found Eze 33 and Testimonies to Ministers &amp; Gospel Workers<br>
to be remarkably relevant.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; 4-- The doctrine of the sanctuary, now being either denied or replaced by</i><br>
<i>&gt; vague uncertainties.</i><br>
<p>
I can assert that a previous pastor at our Tempe church denied the existence<br>
of a heavenly sanctuary and claimed believing in such was unnecessary.<br>
When gently questioned (during a mid-week meeting), he referred to his<br>
Seminary classes.  Since I find the body of Scriptural and SoP evidence<br>
strongly supportive of a heavenly sanctuary (e.g., 2 Cor 5, Heb 9), his<br>
statements certainly gave me pause re what he was taught.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I believe he is demanding that something be either black or white,</i><br>
<i>&gt; when it may really be gray.</i><br>
<p>
This is the claim of "Issues" (granted I've only read the Nov insert and<br>
the Dec article in the Review).  However, are these areas really gray?<br>
Scripture is generally pretty clear, when studied in depth and as a whole<br>
(e.g., I Thess 4:13).  As above mentioned above, a thorough study of<br>
Scripture and SoP, under the guidance of the Holy Spirit, should clarify,<br>
esp since sanctuary issues are pillars/landmarks.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I believe he is introducing a spirit of</i><br>
<i>&gt; divisiveness and criticism toward the denomination, instead of working to</i><br>
<i>&gt; make positive change.</i><br>
<p>
Rom 16:17 ties divisiveness to false doctrine, not truth (cf. I Cor 1:10).<br>
If his claims are demonstrably false per the authority and testimony of<br>
Scripture and SoP (and it is unquestionably justified to include EGW<br>
testimonies since historicity is in question), then he would be<br>
considered divisive.  But if his claims are true, by the same criteria,<br>
then he is seeking the unity of the Spirit and of the faith (Eph 4:3,13),<br>
which Christ prayed of the Father.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
