[Ademir P. Soares writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; [ re a friend &amp; her daughter - divorced husband/father is "DisneyLand Dad" ]</i><br>
<i>&gt; I am not one to run away from my problems but I do NOT</i><br>
<i>&gt; want to lose my daughter to the world. What should I do?</i><br>
<p>
Fortify her mind with the stories of Joseph, Daniel, Esther, Namaan's<br>
maid, and Moses.  Each one of these was taken away from godly parental<br>
influence at varying young (and sometimes tender) ages but stayed faithful.<br>
Get Quiet Hour's video "For Such a Time" (re Esther) and talk about<br>
the challenges she faced, the decisions she made, and their consequences.<br>
Claim Isa 54:13 and 49:25.  On becoming a prayer warrior, we found<br>
Mary Chapian's "Of Whom the World Was not WOrthy" insightful (and<br>
very interesting, given the current crisis in Yugoslavia).<br>
