<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;earth, good or bad, happens only with His consent.  Any sentence which</i><br>
<i>&gt;begins with the words "God can't...." is by definition false.  (However, as</i><br>
<i>&gt;I write, I realize there is a counterexample in the Bible.  Can anyone find</i><br>
<i>&gt;it?) </i><br>
<p>
"God cannot be tempted, neither does He tempt anyone" James 1:13<br>
Actually, there are many things that God cannot do, not because He doesn't<br>
have the power to do them, but because they are not in harmony with His<br>
character.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;In the Old Testament God takes credit for both good and evil things that</i><br>
<i>&gt;happen.  To ascribe anything less to Him is to strip Him of His omnipotence.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Any power that the devil has is given at the express consent of God.</i><br>
<p>
"Shall we accept good from God, and not trouble?" Job 2:10<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
