<i>&gt; The opposite would be a broken relationship with God, which would lead to </i><br>
<i>&gt; wrong thoughts and attitudes and thus to wrong actions.  All three of</i><br>
<i>&gt; these levels would be sin, but it was all curable through a restoration</i><br>
<i>&gt; of the relationship with God.</i><br>
<p>
Did Adam have a right relationship with God ?<br>
<p>
Did Adam sin ?<br>
<p>
Was it a broken relationship that lead him to sin ?<br>
<p>
What did break Adam's relationship ?<br>
<p>
"But your iniquities have separated between you and your God, and your sins<br>
    have hid His face from you, that He will not hear." Isa 59:2<br>
<p>
No Adam did not sin because he had a bad relationship, it was his sin that<br>
broke a good relationship.<br>
<p>
Did Adam's broken relationship now mean he kept on sinning ?<br>
<p>
No Adam did not keep on sinning, he fixed the relationship and did not sin<br>
again after that.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
