America being a wolf in lambs clothing isn't new.  You don't even have to get<br>
biblical support for it.  Just ask Native Americans, and other colonized places<br>
like Panama.  Of course other countries are beasts too, and there are other<br>
victims in those cases.<br>
<p>
But I guess what is supposed to make us different is that "lambs clothing"<br>
some would call it drag.  I'm curious as to what the "lamb-likeness" thing is<br>
all about.  What are the exact actions, ideologies etc. which make "it" seem<br>
harmless, before it "undresses" or stops acting like a lamb?<br>
<p>
Poor over exposed Billy Ray isn't the only one.  There are others more<br>
cunning, less questioned: Pat Robertson and all the brain children he's now<br>
spinning off; Lou Sheldon; nice people who do some nice things - sometimes.<br>
