<title>Apr_1993: Visions of...what?</title>
<h1>Visions of...what?</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>06 Apr 1993 20:07:52 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#148">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#148">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#148">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#148">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0149.html">David E. Johnson: "Gospel, etc."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0147.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  The Sovereignty of God"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This is intended to be quite a specific question rather than a broad "theories<br>
of inspiration" one.<br>
<p>
Some have referred to Ellen White's early visions as the original great<br>
controversy visions. She reports seeing and experiencing many events from<br>
the beginning of time right through, all the while accompanied by her angel<br>
guide and friend. Such was the realism of the experience at times that, once<br>
the vision was over, she stated that she felt homesick for heaven.<br>
<p>
Now some of the things she saw were clearly allegorical, such as the steep<br>
winding path with the light at the bottom and Jesus at the top. With other<br>
things it's harder to tell.<br>
<p>
My question is, do we have a means to distinguish between an actual<br>
"historical" (past or future) event which she was shown, and an allegorical<br>
image? Does she distinguish clearly herself? Do we try to err on the side<br>
of assuming things are historical?<br>
<p>
This question is not addressed towards the issue of discrepancies between<br>
Ellen White and professional historians, by the way. Those don't bother me,<br>
but there are some other things that I need to sort out!<br>
<p>
Looking forward to your replies...<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0149.html">David E. Johnson: "Gospel, etc."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0147.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  The Sovereignty of God"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
