<title>Apr_1993: Necessity of Divinity of Christ</title>
<h1>Necessity of Divinity of Christ</h1>
Tim Swensen (<i>swensen@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 7 Apr 1993 11:24:29 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#176">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#176">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#176">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#176">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0177.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Original sin"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0175.html">Steven Timm: "Re: The real issues?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0314.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Necessity of Divinity of Christ"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
Ruben asks why Christ's nature needed to have a divine component (is this the <br>
right way to say it?) while on earth.  The obvious (?) answer relates to the <br>
scope of His sacrifice.  It seems to me that only a divine being (namely the <br>
creator) could make atonement for the sins of ALL men.  I can make atonement<br>
for my own.  This atonement would entail my eternal death, for such is the <br>
paycheck which is due me for my sin.  I cannot atone for anyone else's sin.<br>
<p>
This point has been made by others.  Now I want to throw the ball back in <br>
Ruben's court now.  Aside from His sinless life, what was special about <br>
Christ, if not the fact that He became the only God-man to ever walk this <br>
earth?  There was something special about Christ's birth (born of a virgin).<br>
If His nature was in no way different than ours, why was He not born through<br>
a normal sexual union?<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
swensen@ecn.purdue.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0177.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Original sin"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0175.html">Steven Timm: "Re: The real issues?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0314.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Necessity of Divinity of Christ"</a>
</ul>
