On Apr 6, 11:52am, Ruben Gonzalez wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: Re: The real issues? (Dr. Ralph Larson)</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; As far as the concept of a remnant within the SDA church, which is a major</i><br>
<i>&gt; critism of all the independant ministries. All I can say is that there only</i><br>
<i>&gt; ever was a remnant of Israel that was saved. and Paul tells us that that</i><br>
<i>&gt; was an example for us who live in the last days. Obviously no all SDAs will</i><br>
<i>&gt; be saved just like all evangelicals will not be saved.</i><br>
<p>
I would agree to a degree, but...just to clarify my position:<br>
<p>
Using your analogy of Israel, I liken Israel (the claimed followers of Christ)<br>
to the Christian world today (all brands and flavors...who claim to be followers<br>
of Christ...hence Christians), not just SDAs.  So as you point out, only a remnant<br>
of Israel was saved, so only a remnant of the Christian world today will be saved.<br>
This would include a remnant of the present day SDA church along with a remnant of<br>
the other present day churches (all brands/flavors).  I say "present day" because<br>
I can not say what changes the SDA church will go through between now and the last<br>
day prior to Christ's 2nd coming...we know the shaking time will certainly weed out<br>
a few.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
