<title>Apr_1993: How to eliminate CB's</title>
<h1>How to eliminate CB's</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 7 Apr 93 18:34:03 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#171">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#171">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#171">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#171">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0172.html">Woody Baker: "Re:  end times"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0170.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Relationships and sin"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Just what the title says this is the official report.<br>
<p>
Don't ask me, I'm going to make many people happy and reduce<br>
bandwidth wastage :^) no more of Ruben's ramblings for a while,<br>
cause I'm going on holidays. Hehehehe :)<br>
<p>
Anyway just had to post some excepts from the offical guidelines on how<br>
to eradicate those evil CB's :^) !!! (Get in before they're gone !)<br>
<p>
In the mean while as my parting gesture I just felt the urge to waste<br>
some more bandwidth, So here goes......<br>
<p>
----------------<br>
<p>
PREAMBLE - It is clear from report received that the dissension caused by many<br>
independent ministries is wide-spread, with a great many of our churches <br>
being affected. In assessing the current situation, it is apparent that:<br>
<p>
1. There is confusion over what each independent ministry espouses.<br>
2. Confusion is created by linking truth with error, and the misquoting of <br>
	Scripture and Spirit of Prophecy.<br>
3. Independent groups have a strategy which focuses on,<br>
	a. interests and new members,<br>
	b. young people<br>
	c. the Church, not outreach to the community.<br>
<p>
4. The attitude of intolerance and criticism is more destructive than teaching.<br>
5. Their basis of authority is Ellen White and perceived "historic Adventism".<br>
6. The plan of not addressing the challenges and concerns created by these<br>
   groups over the past decade and not responding to their insidious <br>
   literature has not worked .<br>
7. Their main method of disseminating their propaganda is by the distribution <br>
   of literature, videos and tapes through person-to-person networking and mail.<br>
8. If we do not pro-actively address the situation the Church runs the very <br>
   real risk of losing more good ministers who are becoming broken in health <br>
   and spirits along with a large number of disillusioned and discouraged <br>
   members.<br>
<p>
IDENTIFYING THE ISSUES<br>
<p>
Following are the main issues and areas of concern that independent ministries<br>
seem to highlight and emphasize:<br>
<p>
A. Theological<br>
<p>
1. Nature of Christ; Righteousness by faith, justification and sanctification;<br>
   Perfection; Eschatology - Sunday laws, etc.; Nature of sin.<br>
2. Nature of inspiration~versions and translations; Role, function and authority<br>
   of Ellen White; Ecclesiology - authority of the Church/remnancy.<br>
3. History of Adventism and Adventist doctrine; Fundamentals, landmarks.<br>
4. Sanctuary, 1844, landmarks.<br>
5. Ecumenicalism and relation to other churches; Standards of the Church.<br>
<p>
B. Church Related<br>
<p>
1. Lack of distinctive, prophetic, historic Adventist preaching; Good News<br>
	Unlimited teachings.<br>
2. Worship, celebration; Lab I and II, N.L.P., Hypnotism.<br>
3. Lack of leadership and apostasy at all levels (including corporate); Use of<br>
	tithe.<br>
4. Church Manual [this was italisized]<br>
<p>
<p>
STRATEGY<br>
<p>
In an endeavor to address the current situation as outlined above and educate <br>
the Adventist community to a proper understanding of the issues, it is<br>
<p>
RECOMMENDED: That<br>
<p>
<p>
[... whole bits left out... ]<br>
<p>
<p>
3g. Asking the [omitted to protect the guilty] Division and [your favorite]<br>
    College to review curriculum content to assess whether:<br>
<p>
	i. In primary and secondary education courses a reliable foundation is<br>
	   being laid for an understanding of inspiration and other identified<br>
	   topics of importance.<br>
<p>
	ii. At [as above] College students in all courses, especi theology, are<br>
	   adequately informed on the key issues, the development of our <br>
	   doctrines and how to relate to the key doctrines biblicallY~<br>
<p>
<p>
4. Continued divisiveness caused my many private organizations and individuals <br>
   be addressed in a proper way which could, and in some cases should, include:<br>
<p>
a. Conferences arranging elders' and ministers' meetings to explain the actions,<br>
   etc., of such groups or itinerant preachers.<br>
<p>
b. Encouraging pastors to keep elders and church boards informed of conflict<br>
   caused by private organizationspersons and steps taken to resolve the<br>
   problems.<br>
<p>
c. Leadership extending an invitation to private organizations to share in<br>
   constructive discussion with a view to resolving differences and issues,<br>
   making surge that in particular the instruction given in Matthew 18 is <br>
   followed, and<br>
<p>
FURTHER: That a copy of Dr Phandl's article entitled "Conflict Resolution in<br>
the Light of the New Testament" to be distributed to ministers and elders, and<br>
FURTHER: If there is no co-operation and reconciliation with private<br>
persons/organisation~, that churches to be encouraged to take the necessary<br>
actions outlined in Scripture.<br>
<p>
[Hey we all know what this means don't we :^) ]<br>
<p>
d. Administration at local conference supporting ministers by endorsing hard<br>
   decisions taken by a local church in respect to such organizations or<br>
   individuals and, in extreme circumstances, and where thought necessary,<br>
   administratively recording by an official executive committee action, the<br>
   conference[']s attitude when a local church refuses or fails to address    <br>
   critical and divisive issues.<br>
<p>
[ This one is even better ]<br>
<p>
5c. Compiling a profile for each independent group or individual operating <br>
   outside the recognized framework of the Church. and that this responsibility<br>
   be assigned to the Division Ministerial Association Secretary.<br>
<p>
6f. Establishing contacts in the [I'm not telling] division and the General<br>
   Conference with agreement that all developments and actions relative to<br>
   private organizations be passed on to this Division for updating elders and<br>
   ministers.<br>
<p>
g. Recommending to the General Conference that the section in the Church Manual<br>
   dealing with church business meetings be rewritten to exclude as voting <br>
   members those that no longer attend church, and ask that they define more<br>
   definitively those who are classified as being "in good and regular    <br>
   standing"<br>
<p>
[I really like this one]<br>
<p>
7b. Keep under review the theology. attitude. activity and promotional<br>
   methods of the different independent ministries operating within the <br>
   territory of the [guess who] Division, with the view of resolving areas of <br>
   misunderstanding and potential conflict and suggesting appropriate action <br>
   when deemed necessary. Power to act and recommend to Division Executive <br>
   Committee.<br>
<p>
c. Develop and implement ongoing strategies and programmer of ministry to<br>
   educate both ministers and church members in those specific areas promoted<br>
   by independent ministry groups which generate misunderstanding of the<br>
   doctrines of the Church and their historical development, or have the <br>
   potential to, or which may cause members t.o lose confidence in the Church <br>
   and its leadership. Power to act and recommend to Division Executive <br>
   Committee.<br>
<p>
d. Appraise various independent ministries and recommend for registration those<br>
   considered to be SUPPORTIVE and review as necessary the guidelines and<br>
   protocol for approving such groups. Power to act and recommend to Division<br>
   Executive Committee.<br>
<p>
<p>
-------------<br>
(Arn't you all lucky you don't know the other half of the story :)<br>
<p>
I won't be answering any questions on the above material so don't ask me !!<br>
<p>
Enjoy my absence, while it lasts, 'cause I'll be back, bigger and better :^)<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
