<title>Apr_1993: Missions and the Bible</title>
<h1>Missions and the Bible</h1>
Malachi Robertson (<i>Malachi.Robertson@lambada.oit.unc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 7 Apr 93 21:32:47 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#180">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#180">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#180">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#180">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0181.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Style"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0179.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Complete overcoming"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I recently was talking to a friend of mine and telling him about how<br>
widespread the missionary work of the SDA Church was.  He then brought up<br>
the question about what we do about giving the Bible to some of the groups<br>
we meet; in other words, if we encounter a group who has a foreign<br>
lanaguage and no Bible in their language what  do we do?  Ian.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
