<!-- body="start" -->
Ruben has brought up the verse several times that iniquities separate<br>
us from God.  I'm not a Greek scholar, and I don't have a Strong's handy.<br>
But I seem to remember that there are shades of meaning between "iniquities",<br>
"transgressions", "sins", and several other things that we would consider <br>
synonyms.  In particular, the word for iniquities has to do with a lack of <br>
faith in God, if I remember correctly.  Can someone check me on this?<br>
<p>
Also, someone made a reference to the "Baker Letter" which has frequently <br>
been quoted by those who want to counter the viewpoints of those who<br>
would say Christ was exactly like humans.  I have read this letter but<br>
again don't have it handy.  If someone does have the text of this letter<br>
available and can summarize it, I'd be much obliged.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
