Good point.  Remember that the Bible was written by men, and given by GOD<br>
for man's education.  Therefore it is inherantly biased toward man.  It is<br>
quite problable that other beings in Gods universe are different.  After all,<br>
GOD made man in HIS image.  It says nothing else.  God likes variety, and <br>
afterall there are many other configurations of matter that are just as<br>
versatile as man's.  I'm looking forward to meeting a whole universe of<br>
diffrent beings.  We already know that certain classes of angles have<br>
four heads, 8 wings, four sets of arms, and apparently some very strange<br>
feet.  So why shouldn't GOD have created other configurations of sentient beings?<br>
Cheers<br>
woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
