<!-- body="start" -->
----&gt;<br>
Does being born separate from God mean that one is born in a "lost" condition ?<br>
if so, then it means the same as original sin.<br>
&lt;----<br>
<p>
The results thereof perhaps, but the "original sin" description given by<br>
Ruben is one I've never come across within the SDA church. It seems that<br>
this original sin concept which is being invoked is a little semantical.<br>
After all, the Scripture says that by one man sin was brought into the world,<br>
and by one man it will be removed. This could probably be termed "original<br>
sin" if it wasn't for the fact that others have created a meaning for the<br>
term that goes beyond the two words in the phrase.<br>
<p>
Just a thought, some of those who hold Ruben's view that a human is born<br>
"saved", or I should say is not born "lost", also believe that life begins<br>
at conception. Perhaps abortion is not so bad after all???<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
