Hi,<br>
<p>
A few weeks ago I attended a Portland area week-end with Ralph Larsen.<br>
I thought it was one of the best week-ends in a long time.  He stuck<br>
to his topics using Bible and EGW.  He was not there to attack the<br>
church.  He did point out that certain Calvinistic doctrines are<br>
being more and more accepted in our church and then used lots of Bible<br>
and some SOP to debunk these theologies.  Some might call that<br>
"attacking the church".  But how do you set the record straight on<br>
popular doctrines if you don't identify them and deal with them.<br>
He was not calling out names and he was not running out dirty laundry<br>
on people.<br>
<p>
True, some of the independents do name names and their dirty deeds.<br>
I don't think that is necessary and so I was most appreciative<br>
Larsen's approach that week-end.<br>
<p>
Friend,<br>
<p>
Dave<br>
