Let me add a few quotes from memory, from the Desire of Ages, for<br>
those who respect the writings of Ellen White:<br>
<p>
Christ's perfect humanity is that which all His followers may possess,<br>
if they will be in subjection to God as He was.<br>
<p>
When we know God as it is our privilege to know him, our lives will be<br>
lives of continual obedience.<br>
<p>
<p>
And there are many more like them.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
