<i>&gt;others have created a meaning for the term that goes beyond the two words in</i><br>
<i>&gt;the phrase.</i><br>
<p>
I came across a very strange meaning for this phrase a few months ago. I was<br>
brousing through the religion conference in the bulletin board in my<br>
university, and they were all talking about whether babies are born<br>
condemned sinners, and the non-christians found this idea ridiculous and<br>
distasteful and said so (you can't teach a baby anything, so how's it<br>
supposed to know how to do anything wrong). Anyway, it seems that the people<br>
in there had the idea that the original sin committed by Adam and Eve was<br>
that they had sexual relations, and so all children born as a result of<br>
sexual reproduction are tainted by sin, except Jesus, who was born to a<br>
virgin. I wonder where they got this ridiculous idea from. Anyway, i showed<br>
them where God Himself told Adam and Eve to multiply, and so that couldn't<br>
be a sin.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
