<title>Apr_1993: Re:  dinosaurs</title>
<h1>Re:  dinosaurs</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@ccpx4.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 12 Apr 93 03:52:40 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#219">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#219">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#219">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#219">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0220.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Humanity of Christ"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0218.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "New organ"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0212.html">Dan Gill: "dinosaurs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;What do all of you believe happened to the dinosaurs?  Did they _really_</i><br>
<i>&gt;exist?  Was it a million years ago?  Were they distroyed in the flood?</i><br>
<i>&gt;Were they a product of the antideluvians fiddling around with genetics?</i><br>
<p>
Yes, they really did exist, there is ample fossil evidence of that. Was it a<br>
million years ago? Well, most scientists think it was more like hundreds of<br>
millions of years ago, while most SDAs think it more like a few thousand<br>
years ago. Were they distroyed by the flood? Well, thats one way to explain<br>
their disappearence. Were they "amalgamations" resulting from antedeluvian<br>
(sounds like "pre-cambrian" or some other geologic word some people like to<br>
use) experiments in genetics? Well, who knows? For all we know of them, the<br>
antedeluvians might even have gone to the moon.<br>
	As far as i know, the bible doesn't specifically mention these<br>
animals, which makes one wonder why, since they must have been pretty hard<br>
not to notice, being so huge and all, but then, Mrs White suggests that<br>
humans were much bigger then too. Still, the bible doesn't say much about<br>
the wildlife before the flood, except when they went into the ark or got<br>
sacrificed.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
