Elaine, thanks for the helpful discussion on dinosaurs.  You may not know<br>
it but here in La Sierra we now have a pair of Tuataras on display in the<br>
World Museum of Natural History.  Many people consider them to be living<br>
dinosaurs. . . they are found continuously in the fossil record back to<br>
the dinosaurs.  From what I have learned about them, skeletally they are<br>
very interesting.<br>
<p>
While you are at it, you might explain findings such as the La Brea Tar<br>
Pits.  It always troubles me that a number of species, especially large<br>
species, survived the flood (in the Ark?) only to become extinct rather<br>
soon after the flood.  It seems like this problem could have been forseen<br>
and would have saved Noah building such a large craft to save them from the<br>
flood.<br>
<p>
Bill<br>
