<title>Apr_1993: Re: Baker letter</title>
<h1>Re: Baker letter</h1>
Noe Torres | ECISD (<i>noe@tenet.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 13 Apr 1993 09:06:40 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#240">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#240">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#240">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#240">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0241.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Baker letter"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0239.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Marriage hints &amp; tips file"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0217.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Baker letter"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0242.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Baker letter"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Mon, 12 Apr 1993, Steven Timm wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Dr. Larson's main lesson that he draws from the nature of Christ seems </i><br>
<i>&gt; to be that it is possible for us to overcome sin through the same power</i><br>
<i>&gt; of God that Christ accessed.</i><br>
<p>
QUESTIONS:<br>
Is this "power of God" separate and independent from the Atonement?  If<br>
not, how is it related to the Atonement?  And if the power that enables us<br>
to overcome sin is separate from the power we receive from Christ as a<br>
result of the Atonement, then what was the point of the whole ordeal<br>
Christ went through?  Was He merely an "example" that we are now also<br>
supposed to follow?  Was He in no way different from one of us?  Are we to<br>
be our own "little saviors"? <br>
<p>
I'm sorry, but if someone suggests that the power that saves me comes from any<br>
source other than Christ and Him Crucified, I smell a rat....  I have a<br>
Savior who, though he clothed Himself in humanity to accomplish His great<br>
mission, remained Creator and King of the Universe.  If someone says that<br>
it was unfair for Him to have any advantage over us, I ask "why?" --- It<br>
is because of Him that we now have every advantage wrought out by Him on<br>
our behalf!  Salvation is all of Christ and none of us.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
