<!-- body="start" -->
 From a message about Adam &amp; sin:<br>
<p>
----&gt;<br>
Adam was with Eve throughout the entire episode.  Yet he allowed Eve to<br>
be the spokesperson about the things of God, abdicating his role as<br>
spiritual head over the family.  He allowed Eve to eat the fruit, while<br>
he stood right by her.  Then he ate some of the fruit himnself.<br>
&lt;----<br>
<p>
Where does the idea come from that Adam was the spiritual head over the<br>
family even before sin? I would have thought that Eve's "connection" with<br>
God was equal to Adam's, and that the concept of a "spiritual head" is<br>
only needed under the rule of sin.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
