<!-- body="start" -->
I initiated this topic to dicuss other beings. However it has evolved into<br>
something interesting and similar to the point I was making aout other<br>
beings. Some have stated that they can't perceive a loving God that reviews<br>
the evil satan causes on a case by case basis and that this would ruin their<br>
image of God. <br>
Why wouldn't the almighty God e ale to keep up with everything that goes on<br>
in a planet that he created (sorry, the above scribble should be 'be able').<br>
Of course he knows and allows the suffering of each individual. Do you you <br>
think he only keeps up with a select few friends? The fact that we think this<br>
is so horrible shows that we aren't looking on a broader scale (which was my<br>
point about other beings). We must remember that God has the entire universe<br>
to consider when making decisions. The great controversy is not just limited<br>
to earth. We are just the unlucky beings who have to deal with satan bothering<br>
us. God does care for those who suffer even when he allows the suffering. We <br>
must keep our faith just as Job did and accept the sovereignty of God.<br>
<p>
Clayton Alves<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
