In response to Sherman's question:( "Does everyone or I should say a vast<br>
majority of adventists believe in the complete overcoming of all sin in this<br>
life thorugh the power of God?" )I would state that it is our goal as<br>
Christians to seek Christ first and let the overcoming of sin be a marvelous<br>
task of the Holy Spirit working within us rather than our own task.  Any<br>
victory over sin is totally the work of Christ and the Holy Spirit working in<br>
our lives.  Is it possible that all sin may be overcome in our lives?  Yes,<br>
with God all things are possible, but the victory is His not ours.  "If we<br>
claim to be without sin we deceive ourselves and the truth is not in us.  If<br>
we confess our sins he is faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and<br>
purify us from all unrighteousness." 1John 1:9.<br>
<p>
Ron Swensen<br>
ron swen@aol.com<br>
