<title>Apr_1993: Re:  Humanity of Christ</title>
<h1>Re:  Humanity of Christ</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 13 Apr 93 21:19:55 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#250">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#250">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#250">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#250">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0251.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Power for victory"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0249.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Re: Humanity of Christ"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0236.html">Paul Gates: "Humanity of Christ"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Nancy Vehymeister writes:<br>
<i>&gt;Yes, it is tremendously important to recognize that Christ was fully human.</i><br>
<i>&gt;I know of no Adventist that would deny that.  My question is whether one</i><br>
<i>&gt;can determine from the evidence what KIND of human nature he had and whether</i><br>
<i>&gt;this determination is vital to salvation or the mission of the church.</i><br>
<p>
I think that the reason why there is so much interest in what sort of human<br>
Jesus was and is, is mainly because people ask if His example is followable<br>
by us. If He was in some way less succeptible to the kind of temptations we<br>
are exposed to, if he did not have our sinful tendencies, then perhaps he<br>
had an advantage over us and so we don't actually have much hope of actually<br>
following Him as a followable example in Christian living.<br>
<p>
Actually, the gospel of salvation is so simple even a child can understand<br>
it, and sometimes i think we make it too complicated and confusing, when all<br>
we have to do is trust and obey.<br>
	The bible says we are to follow Jesus, to be like Him, that we will<br>
have help in doing so, that we will never be tempted beyond what we are able<br>
to bear, that it is God and not us, that will transform our characters --<br>
all we have to do is go along with Him and trust Him, that Jesus is our<br>
saviour from sin, that is what His name means. It also says that Jesus was<br>
tempted in all points as we are, so he knows how its like and can help us<br>
when we are tempted, it also says he was without sin.<br>
	As far as i'm concerned, if Jesus took all the trouble to become a<br>
man and live among us sinners, becoming so much like us, although He is God,<br>
that most people couldn't recognise Him, to show us how to live, then why<br>
don't we just follow Him and not worry so much about it. Trust and obey,<br>
there's no other way, to be happy in Jesus but to trust and obey. Simple as<br>
that.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
