<title>Apr_1993: Can we all get along?</title>
<h1>Can we all get along?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 14 Apr 1993 00:39:23 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#255">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#255">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#255">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#255">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0256.html">TANG BENG YONG: "THE NATURE OF JESUS THE CHRIST"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0254.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Power for victory"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0300.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Can we all get along?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Or, which syllable of Ad-ven-tist do YOU stress]<br>
<p>
In a couple days we will find out if our country has learned anything <br>
from the last spate of riots.  It's also an opportune time to consider<br>
whether our church has made any progress over the last year.  <br>
In the suburbs of Chicago and in the field of high-energy physics I am <br>
rather isolated from the problem of race relations currently.  I have <br>
the strong feeling that the kids I work with are more isolated and<br>
sheltered than myself.  They have no idea what it would be like to live<br>
in the inner<br>
city or a third-world country.  And there are only 12 African Americans<br>
out of 2000 or so people in my field.  <br>
<p>
The walls of organizational apartheid in the SDA church are still high.<br>
There is no overall strategy to reach the city of Chicago because the <br>
black conference wants to do it one way and the white conference another.<br>
(The union office was able to reach agreement for a strategy in Detroit,<br>
so I'm not sure what the holdup is.)  <br>
<p>
But I've talked to enough leaders and grass-roots people to realize that<br>
there are real reasons why the "agenda" of black leaders in the SDA<br>
church<br>
is different from that of white leaders is different from that of<br>
hispanic leaders is different from............  Rather than trying to<br>
impose a solution on both sides, we need to look at the basic inequities<br>
which still remain in our system and work on removing them so we can<br>
finally come to one accord.  There is a window of time in which we still<br>
speak the same language<br>
and understand each other's terms.  During this short window,<br>
communication is possible.  After that, I'm afraid the groups may<br>
diverge.<br>
<p>
I'm concerned not because the record is bad in Illinois, but the record <br>
is in fact fairly good, and we are still a long ways apart.  Illinois<br>
Conference has a good record of diversity, and I want to see that<br>
continue.<br>
Another good sign is that James Humphries, church ministries director <br>
for Lake Region, came to our big youth rally this spring and extended<br>
his hand in a call for collaboration and cooperation.  We are trying to<br>
make<br>
as good use of this opportunity as we can.<br>
<p>
Diversity quiz:  Check and see how well you know your brethren and sistern<br>
in the Regional Conferences:  the Ad-VEN-tists<br>
<p>
1)  Where is the nearest regional conference church to your house<br>
(West coast use nearest predominantly AfAm)<br>
(In some white churches 50% of the members don't know this answer).<br>
<p>
2)  How many of its members do you know on a first-name basis?<br>
<p>
3)  What is the name of the magazine where they will get news of the fellow<br>
churches in their conferences?<br>
<p>
4)  How many meetings on average will they have at their church during<br>
the course of a week?<br>
<p>
5)  Are chitlings something that you might find served at a potluck there?<br>
<p>
6)  Did their basketball team win lots of games in the current season?<br>
Has your church ever played them in basketball or any other sport?<br>
<p>
<p>
Or check and see how well you know your brethern and sistern in the<br>
white conferences, the AD-ven-tists.<br>
<p>
1)  Where is the nearest white-conference church to your house?<br>
<p>
2)  How many of its members do you know on a first-name basis?<br>
<p>
3)  Where is the nearest white-conference camp to your house?  Have<br>
you ever received any brochures about it?  Been there?<br>
<p>
4)  Where is the nearest white-conference boarding academy to your house?<br>
Do any children from your church attend?<br>
<p>
5)  Where is the nearest day church school to your house?  Do children<br>
from your church attend?  Are you welcome to use the gym if such exists?<br>
<p>
<p>
For both groups:<br>
When was the last time your local church collaborated with one from the <br>
other conference on anything?<br>
<p>
<p>
Bonus questions:  <br>
1)  Give the name of the first man God spoke to in or near 1844,<br>
giving visions similar to those of Ellen White.<br>
<p>
2)  What is the local congregation with the largest amount of weekly<br>
tithe in North America?<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
