<!-- body="start" -->
On Tue, 13 Apr 1993, Steven Timm wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; The power of God is the power that is bestowed through the Atonement.</i><br>
<i>&gt; In my mind the purpose of the Atonement is to cleanse the people of God </i><br>
<i>&gt; from sin.  This power to overcome is every bit a free gift, just like</i><br>
<i>&gt; justification.</i><br>
<p>
I think the Atonement is much more than a cleansing from sin.  It is the<br>
great mystery of all time that even the angels are awed by.  It is by the<br>
Atonement that healing will eventually come to a universe stricken with<br>
the cancer of sin.  EGW says that even the heavenly beings are not secure<br>
except by looking to the Atonement.... an awesome thought.  EGW also says<br>
that we don't really understand the full implications of what happened at<br>
Calvary as we should.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
