<!-- body="start" -->
On 13 Apr 1993 HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; I like to think of Christ as 100% human and</i><br>
<i>&gt; 100% divine. </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
Pam, I think you are 100% correct.  The only "asterisk" being that Christ's<br>
spiritual nature was never touched by sin as ours is.  Had he in His mind<br>
given in to sin, all would have been lost; thus, He accomplished that<br>
which Adam and Eve failed to do: remain faithful and unaffected by the<br>
enemy's temptations.  This is why the Bible refers to Christ as the Second<br>
Adam.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
