<!-- body="start" -->
On Tue, 13 Apr 1993, David Plaisted wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; In response to Noe Torres, I believe that without Christ's atonement</i><br>
<i>&gt; we would be cut off from God and not have access to power for</i><br>
<i>&gt; victory over sin.</i><br>
<p>
Wonderfully stated, David.  I agree completely.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Since Pentecost the Holy Spirit has been poured out in fuller measure.</i><br>
<p>
The Spirit, though, does not act independently of Christ or independently<br>
of His Atoning work.  The Spirit ministers to each believer the<br>
fruits (benefits) of Christ's Atonement.  Christ said that the Spirit<br>
would not speak of Himself.  The power imparted by the Spirit to us is not<br>
a power that is independent of Christ -- it is an extension of Christ's<br>
glorious victory at the cross, in my opinion.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
