Bill, thanks for the request for info on Rancho La Brea.  I've been to the<br>
Page Museum several times and have spent time exploring the paleo rooms with<br>
George Jefferson as our guide.  He has been doing some really interesting<br>
research in the past five years but I'm not sure just what has been published.<br>
I'm too swamped to pursue this right now so please be patient with me.  I'll<br>
try to put something together on this soon.  The explanation of the deposit is<br>
a little more complex than the scenario presented by the museum film.  For<br>
those who are not aware:  Rancho La Brea is a park and museum in downtown Los<br>
Angeles.  The region consists of tar pits, natural seeps of oil/tar and a rich<br>
late Pleistocene fauna (mammals, rodents, birds, insects...) preserved in the<br>
deposits.  Elaine<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
