<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;He [Adam] allowed Eve to eat the fruit, while he stood right by her.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Then he ate some of the fruit himself.</i><br>
<p>
To imply that Adam sinned by not interfering with Eve's decision to<br>
eat the fruit is to imply that Eve did not have freedom of choice and<br>
was not, therefore, fully human. Is this what you meant to imply by<br>
discussing "spiritual headship?" Each had a choice and each made<br>
that choice for perhaps different reasons. But wasn't each individual<br>
totally responsible for that decision? <br>
<p>
Pam Harris<br>
Harrisp@utkvx.utk.edu<br>
