<title>Apr_1993: Re: Spiritual head of the family</title>
<h1>Re: Spiritual head of the family</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 14 Apr 93 16:33:58 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#263">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#263">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#263">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#263">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0264.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Distinctives"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0262.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Terrible Lizards."</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0229.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Spiritual head of the family"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0267.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Re: Spiritual head of the family"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
bruceh@wv.mentorg.com (Bruce Holm) writes:<br>
<i>&gt;I don't disagree that Eve had a good "connection" with God just as Adam did.</i><br>
<i>&gt;But I think there can be only one head of a household and since Adam was</i><br>
<i>&gt;given dominion over the animals he was thereby placed in a position of</i><br>
<i>&gt;leadership.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Just as you run into trouble in a house where you have two heads of the</i><br>
<i>&gt;house in other areas, I believe that you will have trouble if you have two</i><br>
<i>&gt;spiritual leaders, particularly if the two spouses don't see eye to eye on</i><br>
<i>&gt;things.</i><br>
<p>
The first time that the bible mentions that the man will rule over the<br>
woman, is in the context of the curse of God on the fallen pair. This seems<br>
to imply that things were different before the fall.  This is speculation,<br>
but i have a notion that before the fall, there would have been no need of<br>
spiritual leaders, or priests of the family or so on, because people were<br>
perfectly spiritual, and there would have been no risk of "trouble in a<br>
house" because they didn't "see eye to eye on things." Ellen White seems to<br>
support this too, in Patriachs and Prophets. Anyway, after the fall, that is<br>
now, things are very different, relationships have changed, but if we<br>
Adventists are so fond of recommending vegetarianism just because that was<br>
how it was like in Eden, why not also similar roles in the family for men<br>
and women? That was how it was in Eden after all. Just some stuff to think<br>
about.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
