I appreciate Steve's point that our love of Christ should be the distinction<br>
between Christians and non-Christians. However the original question of<br>
distinctives was addressed more towards the evangelical statement of beliefs.<br>
Clearly Ruben was trying to point something out by asking us did we think<br>
we should all be Seventh-day Baptists, I would very much like to know what<br>
that was.<br>
<p>
Please don't misunderstand, I am the last person to say we should dwell on<br>
our distinctives. I am not trying to make a big issue out of this. It's just<br>
that I am putting forth a serious effort to discover exactly what all of<br>
those guys believe, and establish where I stand on all of it. Again, if you<br>
are willing to prepare a brief summary of what you think should distinguish<br>
"Seventh-day Adventist Christian" from "Seventh-day Baptist Christian", and<br>
you are worried about starting an argument, send it direct to me!<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
