On Thu, 13 May 1993, Marcus Stringer wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Again we must come to the essence of it all... Jesus Christ and</i><br>
<i>&gt; Him crucified.  If we try to get into the sheep fold bypassing the</i><br>
<i>&gt; "Gate", we become thieves.</i><br>
<p>
AMEN.  Turn your eyes upon Jesus....  The most wonderful "works" of<br>
Christianity have been accomplished by men and women whose eyes were fixed<br>
upon Christ and who did what they did NOT out of a sense of obligation,<br>
but rather out of a sense of love and appreciation for what Christ has<br>
done for them.  This is the "service of love," which is the only service<br>
acceptable to God.  To seek to do God's will out of a sense of urgency or<br>
obligation indicates the "sullen submission of a rebel" -- not really<br>
trusting in God, but afraid to be lost.<br>
<p>
As we seek to do Christ's will out of gratitute, love, appreciation for<br>
His wonderous love toward us -- without reference to church politics,<br>
without concern for our well-being or our own salvation, without any<br>
self-centeredness -- then we are close to the answer.  And the answer will<br>
reveal that as we draw closer to Christ, we will more clearly see our own<br>
imperfections and flaws in the light of His glorious character.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
 <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
