<!-- body="start" -->
Tang Beng Yong replies to Sue Harrington who replied to Bruce Holm:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I sense a battle of the sexes brewing. Actually, i didn't see Bruce say</i><br>
<i>&gt;anything about females not being on the net or them not being</i><br>
<i>&gt;technologically ept. He was concerned with gender roles in the family, for</i><br>
<i>&gt;which he does have scriptural support, but which i pointed out, probably</i><br>
<i>&gt;were noy the same for Adam and Eve before they rebelled against God, but</i><br>
<i>&gt;were rather, given by God as a result of sin entering this world.</i><br>
<p>
... and other words to keep the issue into perspective...<br>
<p>
But I write:<br>
<p>
Tang, I don't want to equating women with animals (actually animals aren't all<br>
that bad) but if you've ever seen people try to help a wounded animal,<br>
you might remember seeing an animal in terror, and fighting off any approach.<br>
This is especially true if humans have harmed it.  The animal doesn't recognize<br>
that the "helpers" are any different from the harmers UNTIL caring action has<br>
been displayed.  Again, women are creatures quite a ways above "animals",<br>
but I hope you see my point.  It is extremely difficult (NOT <br>
impossible) for many<br>
women to separate the harm done to them.  And how much more difficult it is to<br>
differentiate when the oppressor has used "God" and "God's will" to abuse and<br>
demean?  The human mind which has seen Jesus is confused and - not often<br>
enough - indignant at this contradiction.  So sometimes men are greeted <br>
with the<br>
"claws" or "teeth" which women have grown to protect themselves.<br>
<p>
These protectors come in a wide diversity of forms from defensive women's<br>
organizations, or offensive organizations, down to sweeping distrust of <br>
males.<br>
Sometimes that distrust appears to, and feels like it rakes us men over <br>
the coals.<br>
Maybe it is their way of saying "IDENTIFY YOURSELF!  Are you those evil<br>
oppressors, or a helper?!"  Remember God is not mocked... we reap what we sow,<br>
and are visited with the iniquities of the fathers upon the children, <br>
THREE and<br>
FOUR generations deep.  We men have found our life in being rulers over women,<br>
I suspect that we must lose _that_ life if we expect to continue <br>
climbing up the<br>
narrow way.<br>
<p>
This is why *we all* need the healing which comes from the Atonement, if not,<br>
we will continue in the values of our traditions.<br>
<p>
Marcus Stringer<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
