Just an update of Union College happenings.<br>
 <br>
Tonight the Computer Club officialy voted in its constitution and voted in<br>
new officers for next school year.  This is the first year to have such a<br>
thing and is a positive step in the right dirrection!!!  We together now<br>
work as one to improve our school's computer system.  We are working on<br>
two games currently to be brought on-line.  Tetris and Othelo.  The<br>
problem is that we are stuck to text only terminals without function keys!<br>
 Terible!!!!<br>
<p>
Today I was talking with Thompson Kay who is a Vice President at Christian<br>
Record Services.  I talked with him about the GC using e-mail.  And<br>
suggestedd we do the same.   PLEASE ANY ONE IN ANY CONFERENCE OR SCHOOL<br>
USING E-MAIL FOR WORK OR OTHER COMMUNICATIONS PLEASE WRITE HIM AND LET HIM<br>
KNOW HOW IT CAN BE USED AND WHY CRS SHOULD BE ON-LINE.   (one thing is for<br>
our reps to communicate better with us.)<br>
	Thompson Kay<br>
	CRS/Divsion for Deaf<br>
	PO Box 6097<br>
	Lincoln, NE  68506<br>
<p>
<p>
If you know of any good ways to get internet cheaply I am still trying to<br>
get Union College onto internet.<br>
<p>
Thanks for your time.<br>
