<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0289.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Spiritual head of the family"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Sue Harrington replies to Bruce Holm:<br>
<i>&gt;"You will have trouble"--to whom are you speaking?  Oh, yes, I forgot the</i><br>
<i>&gt;assumption in this technological arena is that the only people on the net</i><br>
<i>&gt;are males.  And, what's more these persons (males) so intent on keeping</i><br>
<i>&gt;control of everything controllable must counsel each other on how to</i><br>
<i>&gt;maintain control of that group of technologically inept persons--women.  I</i><br>
<i>&gt;hope you have a great deal of trouble from the person you wish to control.</i><br>
<p>
I sense a battle of the sexes brewing. Actually, i didn't see Bruce say<br>
anything about females not being on the net or them not being<br>
technologically ept. He was concerned with gender roles in the family, for<br>
which he does have scriptural support, but which i pointed out, probably<br>
were noy the same for Adam and Eve before they rebelled against God, but<br>
were rather, given by God as a result of sin entering this world. <br>
<p>
<i>&gt;The Holy One created us all to have an individual relationship with Her.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Any person interferring with that divine relationship is stepping out</i><br>
<i>&gt;their human condition/position and attempting to play God--but then</i><br>
<i>&gt;isn't that what a great many males do and use the scriptures to</i><br>
<i>&gt;justify in this group of believers.</i><br>
<p>
This is new to me. Are you suggesting that God is female? All along, i had<br>
the impression that if God has gender, then God must be male, because the<br>
bible always uses "He" and "His" and so on, to refer to God. The only place<br>
that i can think of where perhaps God is described as female is when Jesus<br>
says that Jesus wished that Jesus could gather the children of Jerusalem<br>
together as a hen gathers chicks under its wings, but this does not mean<br>
that Jesus is female any more than it means that Jesus is a chicken.<br>
	Bruce did not say anything to suggest that females have any less of<br>
a relationship with God than do males. Gender roles have nothing to do with<br>
one's relationship with Him (or Her or It?) any more than being a house slave<br>
means that one cannot be a christian. (Philemon was a slave right?)<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
