<title>Apr_1993: Dwain Ford Symposium</title>
<h1>Dwain Ford Symposium</h1>
Rick Cook (<i>rlcook@erenj.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 16 Apr 93 10:16:54 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#296">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#296">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#296">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#296">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0297.html">McCluskey G: "Project Gutenberg"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0295.html">Scott  Bechtel: "Union"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
        The following is the schedual for the symposium honoring the<br>
retirement of Prof. Dwain Ford from the chemistry department at Andrews<br>
University.  The symposium will be followed by a banquet and tribute.  <br>
<p>
<p>
               Dwain Ford Symposium in Chemistry<br>
<p>
                        April 23, 1993<br>
<p>
9:30 am	        "Styrene-co-Acrylonitrile Process Research:  Inhibiting the<br>
			             Formation of Static SAN Layers"<br>
                Debra R. Navarro - Research Chemist, Designed<br>
Thermoplastics<br>
                Research.  The Dow Chemical Company.<br>
<p>
9:55 am	        "Pressure - Induced Crossover from Good to Poor Solvent<br>
Behavior<br>
 		             for Polyethylene Oxide in Water"<br>
		              Richard Cook - Doctoral Candidate, Harvard University.<br>
<p>
10:20 am	       "A New Moldable Foam for Casting Ferrous Materials Without<br>
 		             Lustrous Carbon Defects"<br>
		              Norman Moll - Senior Associate Scientist, Applied Organics<br>
and<br>
 		             Functional Polymers.  The Dow Chemical Company.<br>
<p>
10:45 am	       "Putting Maxwell's Demon To Work, Membrane Gas Separation--<br>
                The Technology and its Scientific Basis"<br>
		              David J. Moll - Research Leader, Advanced Polymeric Systems<br>
                Laboratory, Central Research and Development.  The Dow<br>
 			            Chemical Company.<br>
<p>
11:10 am	       "Synthesis and Affinity of Electrophilic Ligands Designed<br>
for<br>
 		             Irreversible Interaction at Optoid Receptors"<br>
		              Rhonda (Payne) Davis - Doctoral Candidate, Department of<br>
 		             Medicinal Chemistry, University of Washington.<br>
<p>
11:35 am	       "Hypericin:  Photophysical Properties of a Potent<br>
Photodynamic<br>
 		             Agent"<br>
		              Jamey Anderson - Doctoral Candidate, University of<br>
California at<br>
 		             Los Angeles.<br>
<p>
12:00 pm	       "A Synthetic Approach to an Organosilicon Starburst<br>
Polymer"<br>
		              David Son - Doctoral Candidate, Massachusetts Institute of<br>
 			            Technology.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
