<title>Apr_1993: Re: Distinctives</title>
<h1>Re: Distinctives</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 16 Apr 93 14:39:04 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#303">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#303">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#303">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#303">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0304.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Iron &amp; vegetarians"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0302.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Iron &amp; vegetarians"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0264.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Distinctives"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0309.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: Distinctives"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Tony Writes:<br>
<i>&gt; Please don't misunderstand, I am the last person to say we should dwell on</i><br>
<i>&gt; our distinctives. I am not trying to make a big issue out of this. It's just</i><br>
<p>
What does "dwell on our distinctives" mean?  How much preaching of our<br>
understanding of scripture is allowed before we cross this line of "dwelling<br>
on our distictives."  How important are the distinctives?<br>
<p>
<p>
I believe this is one of the points Ruben was trying to get to.  What is the<br>
big difference between other churches and the Seventh-Day Adventist Church?<br>
Does our existance call for a preaching of the distinctives?  Are we to be<br>
different from other churches?<br>
<p>
I do not believe these questions are easy ones to answer.  We need supernatural<br>
help to answer them.  God will help us if we work toward the answers.<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"Competition is the law of the jungle.
 Cooperation is the law of civilization."  -  Eldridge Cleaver
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
