<!-- body="start" -->
	I'm not a nutritionist, but I did read a "pro-vege" article in a<br>
weight lifting mag. (believe it or not), that warned about knowing which<br>
vitamins and minerals hinder or detract from each other when eaten<br>
together.  This is probably what is the root cause of some "difficult to<br>
absorb" irons.  There is much more to nutrition than what the average<br>
vege knows.<br>
	A curious note... is the meat and poultry industry in anyway<br>
associated with this article being written?  If so the council to eat meat<br>
would be like, and car industry encouraging us away from public<br>
transit because of it is "unsafe."<br>
<p>
MarcusS<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
