I recently read in Vol 108, No3 of the Australian Edition of Signs of the<br>
Times, that there are Sabbath-keeping and only-clean-food eating groups of<br>
Christians and Jews in the Ethiopean countryside, and the article explains<br>
that they are probably SDAs who went underground out in the countryside and<br>
so survived Mengistu's Red Terror of the 1970s. However, i seem to remember<br>
reading in the Great Controversy and in one of those apologetical books<br>
about the Sabbath, that these are in fact, indiginous Sabbath Keepers of<br>
Pre-SDA origin, who kept the Sabbath freely until Musolinni invaded Ethiopea<br>
or something like that. Can anyone shed light on this?<br>
