of being an SDA which are at least of equal importance as the things that<br>
distinguish us from other Christians. I am the last person to say we<br>
should concentrate mainly on our distinctives, when it seems many today lack<br>
even the basics of Christianity. Besides, the reason for this post is<br>
to assist me in establishing what others believe those distinguishing<br>
factors to be, rather than to discuss how much preaching and<br>
evangelizing should be done about them."<br>
