<!-- body="start" -->
In the long article from Dennis Priebe, the periodical Evangelica was <br>
mentioned several times.  This periodical was active during the height<br>
of the Desmond Ford debate, published in the southwestern Michigan <br>
SDA colony if I understand it right, between 1980 and 1982.  Our family<br>
was on their mailing list.  The article quotes Francis Campbell, at the <br>
time president of the South African Union, without making clear that<br>
at the time he stood firmly in that camp and actually left the church <br>
for a short time and then later returned.<br>
<p>
I find it strange that the doctrine on righteousness by faith is declared<br>
to be "Historical Adventism" by the <br>
Our Firm Foundation crowd (of which Priebe is a member in good standing).<br>
The 1888 Message Study Committee argues just as loudly that the message<br>
of righteousness by faith has never been accepted by the church as a whole,<br>
and I would have to say they are right.<br>
<p>
If our theology is based on one translation of the English bible over<br>
the other (which it may be in some cases because the pioneers didn't<br>
know Greek), then we have a problem.  If people want to use the small<br>
wording <br>
changes as noted by Ruben to avoid acknowledging the truths of Adventism,<br>
then they are looking for excuses anyway.  <br>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
[Note how I combined responses to two posts in one.  A good idea, more of <br>
you should try it.  SCT]<br>
