Hi, I just got this mail from a friend of mine in Texas names Sharon Teo.<br>
-beng<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<p>
During lunch, I wittnessed a 'live' tv telecast on CBS news (with my sis)<br>
of the Branch Davidian Complex burning down.....so looks like its gonna be<br>
over soon!<br>
<p>
It seems that the Fbi agents got tired of waiting and decided to<br>
"encourage" those pple in the compound to get out by pumping in some tear gas<br>
into the complex.  They did it at 6 a.m.<br>
<p>
At about 11:45am they saw a small explosion and the building caught fire.<br>
They reported that according to their surveilence cameras they(FBI) said<br>
they saw 2 men, whom they believe to be cult members starting a fire on<br>
each corner of the complex.<br>
<p>
several pple ( abt 4) ran out of the complex, and when I left, the whole<br>
complex was in ruins.....nothing was left standing, except the flagpole <br>
.......and, guess what?.........they still couldn't find Koresh , the rest<br>
of the adults and the supposedly 70 children!!  they did mention that they<br>
may be hiding in an underground bunker, but they said that they wouldn't<br>
survive 'cos the fire above wld suck all the oxygen from the bunkers.<br>
<p>
In case you're wondering abt fire engines....yeah.....2 came at about<br>
12:40pm!!!<br>
<p>
They kept repeating statements from the White House stating that the FBI<br>
was not responsible for the fire 'cos they said the levels of tear gas<br>
used were not poisonous and that tear gas was not flammable, etc.<br>
<p>
Anyway, another friend of mine watched a CNN broadcast at abt 1:30pm. <br>
Their version of what happened is , well....not the same!!<br>
<p>
They reported that (I think) about 6 pple are in the FBI's custody and<br>
that 2 of them are seriously injured. <br>
<p>
They reported that to pump the tear gas into the complex, they used an <br>
amoured vehicle(tank?) to drill a hole into the wall.<br>
They said that it was the FBI's fault 'cos by doing that, they caused some<br>
damage....like wires and stuff, I think, which caused a fire to ignite,<br>
and which later caused the explosion, etc.....no mention of 2 cult members<br>
starting fires!!!!<br>
<p>
to date, they haven't found anyone else.<br>
<p>
I guess this marks the end of the standoff......maybe.....but I guess its<br>
not going to be over till they find Koresh and the rest!!<br>
<p>
Ohyah.....it seems Koresh replied, when asked by those in the compound-<br>
when they would leave the compound, koresh said that they would leave<br>
 when they saw God's face.<br>
<p>
Anyway, I'll watch the news at 6 pm (in 10 mins.) and I'll keep you updated.<br>
<p>
Sharon.<br>
